{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_0154WzD7RuRZza38mBt9QFhc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01JcjQmXrvqQqQRAuS29L6Pj","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7091,"cache_read_input_tokens":88488,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7091,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":591},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"820d0e7c-d58b-4a93-a67b-6cdd412ba398"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P1rpJWDajBsHtr8xK9uhfn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.HashMap;\n    19→import java.util.Map;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    23→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    24→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    25→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    26→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    27→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    28→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.MessageProducerService;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    33→\n    34→/**\n    35→ * REST Resource for testing and monitoring messaging functionality.\n    36→ * \n    37→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    38→ * \n    39→ * This replaces PingServlet2MDBQueue and PingServlet2MDBTopic servlets\n    40→ * which were used to test JMS messaging in the original application.\n    41→ * \n    42→ * Original endpoints:\n    43→ *   /ejb3/PingServlet2MDBQueue - Send test message to TradeBrokerQueue\n    44→ *   /ejb3/PingServlet2MDBTopic - Send test message to TradeStreamerTopic\n    45→ * \n    46→ * Quarkus endpoints:\n    47→ *   /rest/messaging/ping/broker - Send ping to broker queue\n    48→ *   /rest/messaging/ping/streamer - Send ping to streamer topic\n    49→ *   /rest/messaging/stats - Get messaging statistics\n    50→ */\n    51→@Path(\"/messaging\")\n    52→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    53→public class MessagingResource {\n    54→\n    55→    @Inject\n    56→    MessageProducerService messageProducer;\n    57→\n    58→    // Use singleton pattern - original MDBStats is not CDI-managed\n    59→    private final MDBStats mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    60→\n    61→    /**\n    62→     * Send a ping message to the trade broker queue.\n    63→     * Replaces PingServlet2MDBQueue functionality.\n    64→     */\n    65→    @POST\n    66→    @Path(\"/ping/broker\")\n    67→    public Response pingBroker(@QueryParam(\"message\") String message) {\n    68→        if (message == null || message.isEmpty()) {\n    69→            message = \"Ping from MessagingResource at \" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n    70→        }\n    71→        \n    72→        messageProducer.sendBrokerPing(message);\n    73→        \n    74→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    75→        response.put(\"status\", \"sent\");\n    76→        response.put(\"destination\", \"trade-broker-queue\");\n    77→        response.put(\"message\", message);\n    78→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    79→        \n    80→        return Response.ok(response).build();\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    /**\n    84→     * Send a ping message to the trade streamer topic.\n    85→     * Replaces PingServlet2MDBTopic functionality.\n    86→     */\n    87→    @POST\n    88→    @Path(\"/ping/streamer\")\n    89→    public Response pingStreamer(@QueryParam(\"message\") String message) {\n    90→        if (message == null || message.isEmpty()) {\n    91→            message = \"Ping from MessagingResource at \" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n    92→        }\n    93→        \n    94→        messageProducer.sendStreamerPing(message);\n    95→        \n    96→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    97→        response.put(\"status\", \"sent\");\n    98→        response.put(\"destination\", \"trade-streamer-topic\");\n    99→        response.put(\"message\", message);\n   100→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   101→        \n   102→        return Response.ok(response).build();\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Get messaging statistics.\n   107→     * Shows statistics for processed messages, timing information, etc.\n   108→     */\n   109→    @GET\n   110→    @Path(\"/stats\")\n   111→    public Response getStats() {\n   112→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n   113→        \n   114→        // MDBStats extends HashMap<String, TimerStat> so iterate directly\n   115→        Map<String, Map<String, Object>> formattedStats = new HashMap<>();\n   116→        \n   117→        for (Map.Entry<String, TimerStat> entry : mdbStats.entrySet()) {\n   118→            TimerStat stat = entry.getValue();\n   119→            Map<String, Object> statMap = new HashMap<>();\n   120→            statMap.put(\"count\", stat.getCount());\n   121→            statMap.put(\"minSeconds\", stat.getMinSecs());\n   122→            statMap.put(\"maxSeconds\", stat.getMaxSecs());\n   123→            statMap.put(\"avgSeconds\", stat.getAvgSecs());\n   124→            formattedStats.put(entry.getKey(), statMap);\n   125→        }\n   126→        \n   127→        response.put(\"statistics\", formattedStats);\n   128→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   129→        \n   130→        return Response.ok(response).build();\n   131→    }\n   132→\n   133→    /**\n   134→     * Reset messaging statistics.\n   135→     */\n   136→    @POST\n   137→    @Path(\"/stats/reset\")\n   138→    public Response resetStats() {\n   139→        mdbStats.reset();\n   140→        \n   141→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n   142→        response.put(\"status\", \"reset\");\n   143→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   144→        \n   145→        return Response.ok(response).build();\n   146→    }\n   147→}\n   148→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"32d7d105-edfa-472f-95ee-421a5512ae1e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GJKqgYUvtmFUavbiSD9ux5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→\n    21→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    22→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    23→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    24→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    25→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    26→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    27→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    28→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    29→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    30→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    31→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    38→ * \n    39→ * 1. Package changed: javax.ws.rs -> jakarta.ws.rs\n    40→ * 2. Simplified dependency injection - no longer using Instance<> with qualifiers\n    41→ * 3. @ApplicationPath is not needed in Quarkus - configure in application.properties\n    42→ */\n    43→@Path(\"quotes\")\n    44→@RequestScoped\n    45→public class QuoteResource {\n    46→\n    47→    @Inject\n    48→    TradeServices tradeService;\n    49→\n    50→    @GET\n    51→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    52→    @Path(\"/{symbols}\")\n    53→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesGet(@PathParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    54→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    @POST\n    58→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    59→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    60→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesPost(@FormParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    61→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    private List<QuoteDataBean> getQuotes(String symbols) {\n    65→        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<>();\n    66→\n    67→        try {\n    68→            String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n    69→            for (String symbol : symbolsSplit) {\n    70→                QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeService.getQuote(symbol.trim());\n    71→                if (quoteData != null) {\n    72→                    quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n    73→                }\n    74→            }\n    75→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    76→            e.printStackTrace();\n    77→        }\n    78→\n    79→        return quoteDataBeans;\n    80→    }\n    81→}\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"49417afb-326e-4f31-aabb-65ccf86726ac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GazmcDUvup7nuR6NmsZBqw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    23→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    24→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    25→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    26→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    27→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    28→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    29→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    30→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    31→\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    38→\n    39→/**\n    40→ * Main Trade REST API resource.\n    41→ * Provides REST endpoints for core trading operations.\n    42→ */\n    43→@Path(\"trade\")\n    44→@RequestScoped\n    45→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    46→public class TradeResource {\n    47→\n    48→    @Inject\n    49→    TradeServices tradeService;\n    50→\n    51→    @GET\n    52→    @Path(\"/market\")\n    53→    public Response getMarketSummary() {\n    54→        try {\n    55→            MarketSummaryDataBean summary = tradeService.getMarketSummary();\n    56→            return Response.ok(summary).build();\n    57→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    58→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n    59→        }\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @POST\n    63→    @Path(\"/login\")\n    64→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    65→    public Response login(@FormParam(\"userID\") String userID, \n    66→                         @FormParam(\"password\") String password) {\n    67→        try {\n    68→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(userID, password);\n    69→            return Response.ok(account).build();\n    70→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    71→            return Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    72→                    .entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    @POST\n    77→    @Path(\"/logout/{userID}\")\n    78→    public Response logout(@PathParam(\"userID\") String userID) {\n    79→        try {\n    80→            tradeService.logout(userID);\n    81→            return Response.ok().build();\n    82→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    83→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n    84→        }\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    @GET\n    88→    @Path(\"/account/{userID}\")\n    89→    public Response getAccount(@PathParam(\"userID\") String userID) {\n    90→        try {\n    91→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n    92→            if (account == null) {\n    93→                return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    94→            }\n    95→            return Response.ok(account).build();\n    96→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    97→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n    98→        }\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    @GET\n   102→    @Path(\"/account/{userID}/profile\")\n   103→    public Response getAccountProfile(@PathParam(\"userID\") String userID) {\n   104→        try {\n   105→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   106→            if (profile == null) {\n   107→                return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   108→            }\n   109→            return Response.ok(profile).build();\n   110→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   111→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   112→        }\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    @GET\n   116→    @Path(\"/account/{userID}/holdings\")\n   117→    public Response getHoldings(@PathParam(\"userID\") String userID) {\n   118→        try {\n   119→            return Response.ok(tradeService.getHoldings(userID)).build();\n   120→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   121→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   122→        }\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    @GET\n   126→    @Path(\"/account/{userID}/orders\")\n   127→    public Response getOrders(@PathParam(\"userID\") String userID) {\n   128→        try {\n   129→            return Response.ok(tradeService.getOrders(userID)).build();\n   130→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   131→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   132→        }\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @POST\n   136→    @Path(\"/buy\")\n   137→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   138→    public Response buy(@FormParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   139→                       @FormParam(\"symbol\") String symbol,\n   140→                       @FormParam(\"quantity\") double quantity) {\n   141→        try {\n   142→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.buy(userID, symbol, quantity, \n   143→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   144→            return Response.ok(order).build();\n   145→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   146→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   147→        }\n   148→    }\n   149→\n   150→    @POST\n   151→    @Path(\"/sell\")\n   152→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   153→    public Response sell(@FormParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   154→                        @FormParam(\"holdingID\") Integer holdingID) {\n   155→        try {\n   156→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.sell(userID, holdingID, \n   157→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   158→            return Response.ok(order).build();\n   159→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   160→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   161→        }\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    @POST\n   165→    @Path(\"/register\")\n   166→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   167→    public Response register(@FormParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   168→                            @FormParam(\"password\") String password,\n   169→                            @FormParam(\"fullname\") String fullname,\n   170→                            @FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n   171→                            @FormParam(\"email\") String email,\n   172→                            @FormParam(\"creditcard\") String creditcard,\n   173→                            @FormParam(\"openBalance\") String openBalance) {\n   174→        try {\n   175→            BigDecimal balance = new BigDecimal(openBalance);\n   176→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.register(userID, password, fullname,\n   177→                    address, email, creditcard, balance);\n   178→            return Response.ok(account).build();\n   179→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   180→            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();\n   181→        }\n   182→    }\n   183→}\n   184→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"399bcaaf-3ac6-4cf3-8733-5eae1cc16b79"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lw4zPoWCgYc4gxVSGrmCVH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    20→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    21→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    22→\n    23→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.OrderMessage;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    30→\n    31→/**\n    32→ * Message-Driven Bean for processing trade orders.\n    33→ * \n    34→ * MIGRATION NOTES - Original Jakarta EE annotations:\n    35→ * --------------------------------------------------\n    36→ * @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    37→ * @TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    38→ * @MessageDriven(activationConfig = { \n    39→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"acknowledgeMode\", propertyValue = \"Auto-acknowledge\"),\n    40→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Queue\"),\n    41→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\"),\n    42→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"subscriptionDurability\", propertyValue = \"NonDurable\") \n    43→ * })\n    44→ * public class DTBroker3MDB implements MessageListener { ... }\n    45→ * \n    46→ * Quarkus Migration:\n    47→ * ------------------\n    48→ * @ApplicationScoped replaces @MessageDriven\n    49→ * @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\") replaces JMS destination config\n    50→ * @Transactional replaces @TransactionAttribute\n    51→ * OrderMessage POJO replaces JMS TextMessage\n    52→ */\n    53→@ApplicationScoped\n    54→public class DTBroker3MDB {\n    55→  \n    56→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    57→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    58→\n    59→  // MIGRATION: @Resource MessageDrivenContext mdc -> Exception propagation for rollback\n    60→  // In Quarkus, throwing an exception triggers rollback instead of mdc.setRollbackOnly()\n    61→\n    62→  @Inject\n    63→  TradeServices trade;\n    64→\n    65→  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    66→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    67→      statInterval = 10000;\n    68→    }\n    69→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    70→  }   \n    71→\n    72→  @PostConstruct\n    73→  void init() {\n    74→    Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:init()\");\n    75→  } \n    76→  \n    77→  /**\n    78→   * Process incoming order messages.\n    79→   * \n    80→   * MIGRATION: This replaces the JMS MessageListener.onMessage(Message) method.\n    81→   * - JMS TextMessage -> OrderMessage POJO\n    82→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"command\") -> message.getCommand()\n    83→   * - message.getIntProperty(\"orderID\") -> message.getOrderID()\n    84→   * - message.getBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\") -> message.isTwoPhase()\n    85→   * - message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\") -> message.getPublishTime()\n    86→   */\n    87→  @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    88→  @Transactional\n    89→  public void onMessage(OrderMessage message) {\n    90→    try {\n    91→\n    92→      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n    93→          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n    94→\n    95→      // MIGRATION: JMS redelivery check removed - Quarkus handles redelivery differently\n    96→      // if (message.getJMSRedelivered()) { ... }\n    97→\n    98→      String command = message.getCommand();\n    99→      if (command == null) {\n   100→        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n   101→        return;\n   102→      }\n   103→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n   104→        /* Get the Order ID and complete the Order */\n   105→        Integer orderID = message.getOrderID();\n   106→        boolean twoPhase = message.isTwoPhase();\n   107→        // MIGRATION: 'direct' property removed - not used in Quarkus version\n   108→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n   109→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   110→\n   111→        try {\n   112→          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n   113→\n   114→          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   115→\n   116→          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   117→\n   118→          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   119→            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n   120→                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   121→                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n   122→                \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   123→                \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   124→                \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   125→          }\n   126→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   127→          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n   128→          // MIGRATION: mdc.setRollbackOnly() -> throw RuntimeException\n   129→          throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to complete order: \" + orderID, e);\n   130→        }\n   131→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n   132→\n   133→        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n   134→\n   135→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n   136→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   137→\n   138→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   139→\n   140→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   141→          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n   142→              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   143→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   144→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   145→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   146→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   147→        }\n   148→      } else {\n   149→        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n   150→      }\n   151→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   152→      // JMS onMessage should handle all exceptions\n   153→      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Exception\", t);\n   154→      // MIGRATION: mdc.setRollbackOnly() -> throw RuntimeException  \n   155→      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTBroker3MDB processing failed\", t);\n   156→    }\n   157→  }\n   158→}\n   159→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"edc1038b-88b0-4279-a5f1-09539bdc76ea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JcjQmXrvqQqQRAuS29L6Pj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    19→\n    20→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.QuoteUpdateMessage;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    26→\n    27→/**\n    28→ * Message-Driven Bean for processing quote update streams.\n    29→ * \n    30→ * MIGRATION NOTES - Original Jakarta EE annotations:\n    31→ * --------------------------------------------------\n    32→ * @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    33→ * @TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    34→ * @MessageDriven(activationConfig = { \n    35→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"acknowledgeMode\", propertyValue = \"Auto-acknowledge\"),\n    36→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Topic\"),\n    37→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\"),\n    38→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"subscriptionDurability\", propertyValue = \"NonDurable\") \n    39→ * })\n    40→ * public class DTStreamer3MDB implements MessageListener { ... }\n    41→ * \n    42→ * Quarkus Migration:\n    43→ * ------------------\n    44→ * @ApplicationScoped replaces @MessageDriven\n    45→ * @Incoming(\"trade-streamer-topic\") replaces JMS destination config\n    46→ * QuoteUpdateMessage POJO replaces JMS TextMessage\n    47→ */\n    48→@ApplicationScoped\n    49→public class DTStreamer3MDB {\n    50→\n    51→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    52→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    53→\n    54→  // MIGRATION: @Resource MessageDrivenContext mdc -> Exception propagation for rollback\n    55→  // In Quarkus, throwing an exception triggers rollback instead of mdc.setRollbackOnly()\n    56→\n    57→  /** Creates a new instance of TradeSteamerMDB */\n    58→  public DTStreamer3MDB() {\n    59→    Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:DTStreamer3MDB()\");\n    60→    \n    61→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    62→      statInterval = 10000;\n    63→    }\n    64→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  /**\n    68→   * Process incoming quote update messages.\n    69→   * \n    70→   * MIGRATION: This replaces the JMS MessageListener.onMessage(Message) method.\n    71→   * - JMS TextMessage -> QuoteUpdateMessage POJO\n    72→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"command\") -> message.getCommand()\n    73→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"symbol\") -> message.getSymbol()\n    74→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"price\") -> message.getNewPrice()\n    75→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"oldPrice\") -> message.getOldPrice()\n    76→   * - message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\") -> message.getPublishTime()\n    77→   */\n    78→  @Incoming(\"trade-streamer-topic\")\n    79→  public void onMessage(QuoteUpdateMessage message) {\n    80→\n    81→    try {\n    82→      Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n    83→          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n    84→      \n    85→      String command = message.getCommand();\n    86→      if (command == null) {\n    87→        Log.debug(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n    88→        return;\n    89→      }\n    90→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"updateQuote\")) {\n    91→        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"\\n\\t symbol = \"\n    92→              + message.getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t current price =\" + message.getPrice() + \"\\n\\t old price =\"\n    93→              + message.getOldPrice());\n    94→        \n    95→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n    96→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    97→\n    98→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:updateQuote\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n    99→\n   100→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   101→          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: \" + statInterval + \" prices updated:\" +\n   102→              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   103→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   104→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   105→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   106→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs() );\n   107→        }\n   108→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n   109→        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage  received ping command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n   110→        \n   111→\n   112→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n   113→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   114→\n   115→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   116→\n   117→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   118→          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n   119→              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   120→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   121→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   122→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   123→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   124→        }\n   125→      } else {\n   126→        Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n   127→      }\n   128→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   129→      // JMS onMessage should handle all exceptions\n   130→      Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB: Exception\", t);\n   131→      // MIGRATION: mdc.setRollbackOnly() -> throw RuntimeException\n   132→      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTStreamer3MDB processing failed\", t);\n   133→    }\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→}\n   137→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"f946d8ef-22c8-42ce-8f24-cac2d4ecd1b8"}
