{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01RV8cTkfKXNKVq61zGSxcVR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013D8Hnvyya1BA7qDA4uR1dJ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/FinancialUtils.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11011,"cache_read_input_tokens":95579,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":11011,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":580},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"96d037ba-262b-45ff-85b9-3b70485f4f40"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014VMQjadCLbhDcfkyMN12Pd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    22→\n    23→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\n    24→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n    25→\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    27→\n    28→/**\n    29→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    30→ * \n    31→ * Original (Jakarta EE - JMS Producer Pattern):\n    32→ * ---------------------------------------------\n    33→ * @Resource(name = \"jms/QueueConnectionFactory\")\n    34→ * private ConnectionFactory queueConnectionFactory;\n    35→ * \n    36→ * @Resource(name = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n    37→ * private Queue tradeBrokerQueue;\n    38→ * \n    39→ * // Usage:\n    40→ * JMSContext context = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();\n    41→ * TextMessage message = context.createTextMessage();\n    42→ * message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\");\n    43→ * message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID);\n    44→ * message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase);\n    45→ * message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    46→ * message.setText(\"Order message...\");\n    47→ * context.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n    48→ * \n    49→ * Quarkus (SmallRye Reactive Messaging - Emitter Pattern):\n    50→ * --------------------------------------------------------\n    51→ * @Inject\n    52→ * @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    53→ * Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter;\n    54→ * \n    55→ * // Usage:\n    56→ * OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    57→ * brokerEmitter.send(message);\n    58→ * \n    59→ * Key Differences:\n    60→ * 1. No ConnectionFactory/JMSContext - just @Channel + Emitter\n    61→ * 2. No manual message creation - just create POJO\n    62→ * 3. No explicit property setting - POJO fields are the properties\n    63→ * 4. Cleaner, more type-safe code\n    64→ * 5. Built-in backpressure handling\n    65→ */\n    66→@ApplicationScoped\n    67→public class MessageProducerService {\n    68→\n    69→    @Inject\n    70→    @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    71→    @io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast\n    72→    Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter;\n    73→\n    74→    @Inject\n    75→    @Channel(\"trade-streamer-topic\")\n    76→    @io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast\n    77→    Emitter<QuoteUpdateMessage> streamerEmitter;\n    78→\n    79→    /**\n    80→     * Queue a new order for asynchronous processing.\n    81→     * This replaces the JMS Queue send in the original DTBroker pattern.\n    82→     * \n    83→     * @param orderID the order ID to process\n    84→     * @param twoPhase whether to use two-phase commit\n    85→     */\n    86→    public void queueOrderForProcessing(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    87→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    88→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:queueOrderForProcessing - sending order \" + orderID);\n    89→        brokerEmitter.send(message);\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    /**\n    93→     * Send a ping message to the trade broker queue.\n    94→     * Used for testing and performance measurement.\n    95→     * \n    96→     * @param text the ping message text\n    97→     */\n    98→    public void sendBrokerPing(String text) {\n    99→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.ping(text);\n   100→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendBrokerPing - sending ping\");\n   101→        brokerEmitter.send(message);\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * Publish a quote update to the streamer topic.\n   106→     * This replaces the JMS Topic publish in the original DTStreamer pattern.\n   107→     * \n   108→     * @param symbol the stock symbol\n   109→     * @param newPrice the new price\n   110→     * @param oldPrice the old price\n   111→     */\n   112→    public void publishQuoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n   113→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, newPrice, oldPrice);\n   114→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuoteUpdate - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n   115→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    /**\n   119→     * Publish a complete quote price change to the streamer topic.\n   120→     * This replaces the full JMS Topic publish in the original TradeDirect pattern.\n   121→     */\n   122→    public void publishQuotePriceChange(String symbol, String company, BigDecimal price,\n   123→            BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high,\n   124→            double volume, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n   125→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, price, oldPrice);\n   126→        message.setCompany(company);\n   127→        message.setOpen(open);\n   128→        message.setLow(low);\n   129→        message.setHigh(high);\n   130→        message.setVolume(volume);\n   131→        message.setChangeFactor(changeFactor);\n   132→        message.setSharesTraded(sharesTraded);\n   133→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuotePriceChange - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n   134→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   135→    }\n   136→\n   137→    /**\n   138→     * Send a ping message to the streamer topic.\n   139→     * Used for testing and performance measurement.\n   140→     * \n   141→     * @param text the ping message text\n   142→     */\n   143→    public void sendStreamerPing(String text) {\n   144→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.ping(text);\n   145→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendStreamerPing - sending ping\");\n   146→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   147→    }\n   148→}\n   149→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"eeb7a8c1-b08c-439f-a204-f956acabbfa3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015pQ6j2oQ7vaMXCfYKzwBzw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    20→ * \n    21→ * Original: JMS TextMessage with properties (command, orderID, twoPhase, direct, publishTime)\n    22→ * Quarkus: Plain Java object (POJO) used with Reactive Messaging\n    23→ * \n    24→ * In Jakarta EE, JMS messages were heavyweight with:\n    25→ * - message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\")\n    26→ * - message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID)\n    27→ * - message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase)\n    28→ * - message.setText(...)\n    29→ * \n    30→ * In Quarkus, we use simple POJOs that are serialized automatically.\n    31→ * This is cleaner, type-safe, and doesn't require JMS infrastructure.\n    32→ */\n    33→public class OrderMessage {\n    34→    \n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_NEW_ORDER = \"neworder\";\n    36→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    37→    \n    38→    private String command;\n    39→    private Integer orderID;\n    40→    private boolean twoPhase;\n    41→    private boolean direct;\n    42→    private long publishTime;\n    43→    private String text;\n    44→    \n    45→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    46→    public OrderMessage() {\n    47→    }\n    48→    \n    49→    // Factory method for new order messages\n    50→    public static OrderMessage newOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    51→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    52→        msg.command = COMMAND_NEW_ORDER;\n    53→        msg.orderID = orderID;\n    54→        msg.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    55→        msg.direct = false;\n    56→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    57→        msg.text = \"Order message for orderID=\" + orderID;\n    58→        return msg;\n    59→    }\n    60→    \n    61→    // Factory method for ping messages\n    62→    public static OrderMessage ping(String text) {\n    63→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    64→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    65→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    66→        msg.text = text;\n    67→        return msg;\n    68→    }\n    69→    \n    70→    // Getters and setters\n    71→    public String getCommand() {\n    72→        return command;\n    73→    }\n    74→    \n    75→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    76→        this.command = command;\n    77→    }\n    78→    \n    79→    public Integer getOrderID() {\n    80→        return orderID;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setOrderID(Integer orderID) {\n    84→        this.orderID = orderID;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public boolean isTwoPhase() {\n    88→        return twoPhase;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setTwoPhase(boolean twoPhase) {\n    92→        this.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public boolean isDirect() {\n    96→        return direct;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setDirect(boolean direct) {\n   100→        this.direct = direct;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   104→        return publishTime;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   108→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public String getText() {\n   112→        return text;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setText(String text) {\n   116→        this.text = text;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    @Override\n   120→    public String toString() {\n   121→        return \"OrderMessage{\" +\n   122→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   123→                \", orderID=\" + orderID +\n   124→                \", twoPhase=\" + twoPhase +\n   125→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   126→                '}';\n   127→    }\n   128→}\n   129→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"bc28de21-6d97-415d-9122-63ea45cf165b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kn4x15dEQ5ZqbMnrff3qw7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    22→ * \n    23→ * Original: JMS TextMessage published to jms/TradeStreamerTopic\n    24→ * Properties: command, symbol, price, oldPrice, publishTime\n    25→ * \n    26→ * Quarkus: Simple POJO with same information, used with Reactive Messaging.\n    27→ * \n    28→ * The DTStreamer3MDB consumed topic messages for:\n    29→ * - \"updateQuote\" command: Log price changes\n    30→ * - \"ping\" command: Health check / performance testing\n    31→ */\n    32→public class QuoteUpdateMessage {\n    33→    \n    34→    public static final String COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE = \"updateQuote\";\n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    36→    \n    37→    private String command;\n    38→    private String symbol;\n    39→    private BigDecimal price;\n    40→    private BigDecimal oldPrice;\n    41→    private long publishTime;\n    42→    private String text;\n    43→    \n    44→    // Additional fields for full quote update (matching original JMS message properties)\n    45→    private String company;\n    46→    private BigDecimal open;\n    47→    private BigDecimal low;\n    48→    private BigDecimal high;\n    49→    private double volume;\n    50→    private BigDecimal changeFactor;\n    51→    private double sharesTraded;\n    52→    \n    53→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    54→    public QuoteUpdateMessage() {\n    55→    }\n    56→    \n    57→    // Factory method for quote update\n    58→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage quoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n    59→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    60→        msg.command = COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE;\n    61→        msg.symbol = symbol;\n    62→        msg.price = newPrice;\n    63→        msg.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n    64→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    65→        msg.text = \"Quote update for \" + symbol + \": \" + oldPrice + \" -> \" + newPrice;\n    66→        return msg;\n    67→    }\n    68→    \n    69→    // Factory method for ping\n    70→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage ping(String text) {\n    71→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    72→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    73→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    74→        msg.text = text;\n    75→        return msg;\n    76→    }\n    77→    \n    78→    // Getters and setters\n    79→    public String getCommand() {\n    80→        return command;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    84→        this.command = command;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public String getSymbol() {\n    88→        return symbol;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n    92→        this.symbol = symbol;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n    96→        return price;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   100→        this.price = price;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public BigDecimal getOldPrice() {\n   104→        return oldPrice;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setOldPrice(BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n   108→        this.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   112→        return publishTime;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   116→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    public String getText() {\n   120→        return text;\n   121→    }\n   122→    \n   123→    public void setText(String text) {\n   124→        this.text = text;\n   125→    }\n   126→    \n   127→    // Additional getters/setters for full quote update fields\n   128→    public String getCompany() {\n   129→        return company;\n   130→    }\n   131→    \n   132→    public void setCompany(String company) {\n   133→        this.company = company;\n   134→    }\n   135→    \n   136→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   137→        return open;\n   138→    }\n   139→    \n   140→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   141→        this.open = open;\n   142→    }\n   143→    \n   144→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   145→        return low;\n   146→    }\n   147→    \n   148→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   149→        this.low = low;\n   150→    }\n   151→    \n   152→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   153→        return high;\n   154→    }\n   155→    \n   156→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   157→        this.high = high;\n   158→    }\n   159→    \n   160→    public double getVolume() {\n   161→        return volume;\n   162→    }\n   163→    \n   164→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   165→        this.volume = volume;\n   166→    }\n   167→    \n   168→    public BigDecimal getChangeFactor() {\n   169→        return changeFactor;\n   170→    }\n   171→    \n   172→    public void setChangeFactor(BigDecimal changeFactor) {\n   173→        this.changeFactor = changeFactor;\n   174→    }\n   175→    \n   176→    public double getSharesTraded() {\n   177→        return sharesTraded;\n   178→    }\n   179→    \n   180→    public void setSharesTraded(double sharesTraded) {\n   181→        this.sharesTraded = sharesTraded;\n   182→    }\n   183→    \n   184→    @Override\n   185→    public String toString() {\n   186→        return \"QuoteUpdateMessage{\" +\n   187→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   188→                \", symbol='\" + symbol + '\\'' +\n   189→                \", price=\" + price +\n   190→                \", oldPrice=\" + oldPrice +\n   191→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   192→                '}';\n   193→    }\n   194→}\n   195→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"9cd89a6e-683f-4915-9350-67ae37a007b7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Pcc9jDzXrFkPxLGCPa58cq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    24→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    25→\n    26→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n    38→ * This replaces the manual \"Populate Database\" action from the Jakarta EE version.\n    39→ */\n    40→@ApplicationScoped\n    41→public class DatabasePopulator {\n    42→\n    43→    @Inject\n    44→    EntityManager em;\n    45→\n    46→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    47→    boolean populateOnStartup;\n    48→\n    49→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    50→    int maxUsers;\n    51→\n    52→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    53→    int maxQuotes;\n    54→\n    55→    @Transactional\n    56→    void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    57→        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n    58→            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n    59→            return;\n    60→        }\n    61→\n    62→        // Check if database already has data (using native SQL since entity names are lowercase)\n    63→        Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n    64→        if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n    65→            Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n    66→            return;\n    67→        }\n    68→\n    69→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n    70→        \n    71→        try {\n    72→            populateQuotes();\n    73→            populateUsers();\n    74→            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    75→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    76→            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    private void populateQuotes() {\n    81→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n    82→        \n    83→        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n    84→            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n    85→            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n    86→            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n    87→            \n    88→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n    89→            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n    90→            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n    91→            quote.setPrice(price);\n    92→            quote.setOpen(price);\n    93→            quote.setLow(price);\n    94→            quote.setHigh(price);\n    95→            quote.setChange(0.0);\n    96→            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n    97→            \n    98→            em.persist(quote);\n    99→            \n   100→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   101→                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n   102→            }\n   103→        }\n   104→        em.flush();\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    private void populateUsers() {\n   108→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n   109→        \n   110→        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n   111→            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   112→            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   113→            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   114→            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   115→            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   116→            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n   117→            \n   118→            if (i == 0) {\n   119→                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000); // uid:0 starts with a cool million.\n   120→            }\n   121→            \n   122→            // Create profile\n   123→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   124→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   125→            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n   126→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   127→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   128→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   129→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   130→            em.persist(profile);\n   131→            \n   132→            // Create account\n   133→            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n   134→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   135→            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   136→            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   137→            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n   138→            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n   139→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   140→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   141→            em.persist(account);\n   142→            \n   143→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   144→                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n   145→            }\n   146→        }\n   147→        em.flush();\n   148→    }\n   149→}\n   150→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"be566396-6cde-4a90-b255-00aff53f1b7c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013D8Hnvyya1BA7qDA4uR1dJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * MIGRATION NOTE: Updated to use RoundingMode enum instead of deprecated BigDecimal constants.\n    26→ */\n    27→public class FinancialUtils {\n    28→\n    29→    public static final RoundingMode ROUND = RoundingMode.HALF_UP;\n    30→    public static final int SCALE = 2;\n    31→    public static final BigDecimal ZERO = new BigDecimal(\"0.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    32→    public static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(\"1.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    33→    public static final BigDecimal HUNDRED = new BigDecimal(\"100.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    34→\n    35→    public static BigDecimal computeGain(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    36→        return currentBalance.subtract(openBalance).setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static BigDecimal computeGainPercent(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    40→        if (openBalance.doubleValue() == 0.0) {\n    41→            return ZERO;\n    42→        }\n    43→        BigDecimal gainPercent = currentBalance.divide(openBalance, SCALE, ROUND)\n    44→                .subtract(ONE)\n    45→                .multiply(HUNDRED);\n    46→        return gainPercent;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static BigDecimal computeHoldingsTotal(Collection<?> holdingDataBeans) {\n    50→        BigDecimal holdingsTotal = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    51→        if (holdingDataBeans == null) {\n    52→            return holdingsTotal;\n    53→        }\n    54→        for (Object obj : holdingDataBeans) {\n    55→            HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) obj;\n    56→            BigDecimal total = holdingData.getPurchasePrice()\n    57→                    .multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    58→            holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal.add(total);\n    59→        }\n    60→        return holdingsTotal.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public static String printGainHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    64→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    65→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    66→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    67→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    68→        } else {\n    69→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    70→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    71→        }\n    72→\n    73→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND) + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    74→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    75→        return htmlString;\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public static String printChangeHTML(double change) {\n    79→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    80→        if (change < 0.0) {\n    81→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    82→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    83→        } else {\n    84→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    85→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    86→        }\n    87→\n    88→        htmlString += change + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    89→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    90→        return htmlString;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public static String printGainPercentHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    94→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    95→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    96→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    97→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    98→        } else {\n    99→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">+\";\n   100→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n   101→        }\n   102→\n   103→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n   104→        htmlString += \"%</FONT></B>)<IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n   105→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n   106→        return htmlString;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public static String printQuoteLink(String symbol) {\n   110→        return \"<A href=\\\"app?action=quotes&symbols=\" + symbol + \"\\\">\" + symbol + \"</A>\";\n   111→    }\n   112→}\n   113→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"32e5608d-0fda-4c68-b79c-51a47a3d2f31"}
