{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_011fYJWxH7afu8GEa7fWzSZU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01TYD9P8RmEDM1wraErfVrRn","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TimerStat.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10313,"cache_read_input_tokens":106590,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10313,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":584},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"b518c322-a156-405b-b2ff-0b3c613530bc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QhWQQ8QxiDVooo9WcD7jgc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.AbstractSequentialList;\n    19→import java.util.ListIterator;\n    20→\n    21→public class KeyBlock extends AbstractSequentialList<Object> {\n    22→\n    23→    // min and max provide range of valid primary keys for this KeyBlock\n    24→    private int min = 0;\n    25→    private int max = 0;\n    26→    private int index = 0;\n    27→\n    28→    /**\n    29→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    30→     */\n    31→    public KeyBlock() {\n    32→        super();\n    33→        min = 0;\n    34→        max = 0;\n    35→        index = min;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    40→     */\n    41→    public KeyBlock(int min, int max) {\n    42→        super();\n    43→        this.min = min;\n    44→        this.max = max;\n    45→        index = min;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    /**\n    49→     * @see AbstractCollection#size()\n    50→     */\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public int size() {\n    53→        return (max - min) + 1;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * @see AbstractSequentialList#listIterator(int)\n    58→     */\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public ListIterator<Object> listIterator(int arg0) {\n    61→        return new KeyBlockIterator();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    class KeyBlockIterator implements ListIterator<Object> {\n    65→\n    66→        /**\n    67→         * @see ListIterator#hasNext()\n    68→         */\n    69→        @Override\n    70→        public boolean hasNext() {\n    71→            return index <= max;\n    72→        }\n    73→\n    74→        /**\n    75→         * @see ListIterator#next()\n    76→         */\n    77→        @Override\n    78→        public synchronized Object next() {\n    79→            if (index > max) {\n    80→                throw new java.lang.RuntimeException(\"KeyBlock:next() -- Error KeyBlock depleted\");\n    81→            }\n    82→            return new Integer(index++);\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        /**\n    86→         * @see ListIterator#hasPrevious()\n    87→         */\n    88→        @Override\n    89→        public boolean hasPrevious() {\n    90→            return index > min;\n    91→        }\n    92→\n    93→        /**\n    94→         * @see ListIterator#previous()\n    95→         */\n    96→        @Override\n    97→        public Object previous() {\n    98→            return new Integer(--index);\n    99→        }\n   100→\n   101→        /**\n   102→         * @see ListIterator#nextIndex()\n   103→         */\n   104→        @Override\n   105→        public int nextIndex() {\n   106→            return index - min;\n   107→        }\n   108→\n   109→        /**\n   110→         * @see ListIterator#previousIndex()\n   111→         */\n   112→        @Override\n   113→        public int previousIndex() {\n   114→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: previousIndex() not supported\");\n   115→        }\n   116→\n   117→        /**\n   118→         * @see ListIterator#add()\n   119→         */\n   120→        @Override\n   121→        public void add(Object o) {\n   122→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: add() not supported\");\n   123→        }\n   124→\n   125→        /**\n   126→         * @see ListIterator#remove()\n   127→         */\n   128→        @Override\n   129→        public void remove() {\n   130→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: remove() not supported\");\n   131→        }\n   132→\n   133→        /**\n   134→         * @see ListIterator#set(Object)\n   135→         */\n   136→        @Override\n   137→        public void set(Object arg0) {\n   138→        }\n   139→    }\n   140→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"9b235614-12d8-463c-bc26-609d314836b3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DBTPTkSiB1KzAw7D1B4eqF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collection;\n    19→import java.util.Iterator;\n    20→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    21→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    22→\n    23→/**\n    24→ * MIGRATION NOTE: This class remains largely unchanged.\n    25→ * In Quarkus, you could also use JBoss Logging or SLF4J.\n    26→ * Quarkus uses JBoss LogManager by default.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class Log {\n    29→\n    30→    private final static Logger log = Logger.getLogger(\"daytrader\");\n    31→\n    32→    public static void log(String message) {\n    33→        log.log(Level.INFO, message);\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2) {\n    37→        log(msg1 + msg2);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    41→        log(msg1 + msg2 + msg3);\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public static void error(String message) {\n    45→        message = \"Error: \" + message;\n    46→        log.severe(message);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static void error(String message, Throwable e) {\n    50→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\" + e.toString());\n    51→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, Throwable e) {\n    55→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3, Throwable e) {\n    59→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public static void error(Throwable e, String message) {\n    63→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    64→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2) {\n    68→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    72→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public static void trace(String message) {\n    76→        log.log(Level.FINE, message + \" threadID=\" + Thread.currentThread());\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    public static void traceInterceptor(String message, Object parm1) {\n    80→        log.log(Level.SEVERE, message, parm1);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1) {\n    84→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \")\");\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2) {\n    88→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \")\");\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3) {\n    92→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \")\");\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4) {\n    96→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \")\");\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5) {\n   100→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \")\");\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6) {\n   104→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \")\");\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6, Object parm7) {\n   108→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \", \" + parm7 + \")\");\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public static void traceEnter(String message) {\n   112→        log.entering(\"Log\", message);\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public static void traceExit(String message) {\n   116→        log.exiting(\"Log\", message);\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public static void stat(String message) {\n   120→        log(message);\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public static void debug(String message) {\n   124→        log.log(Level.FINE, message);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public static void print(String message) {\n   128→        log(message);\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public static void printObject(Object o) {\n   132→        log(\"\\t\" + o.toString());\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n   136→    public static void printCollection(Collection c) {\n   137→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   138→        if (c == null) {\n   139→            return;\n   140→        }\n   141→        Iterator it = c.iterator();\n   142→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   143→            log(\"\\t\\t\" + it.next().toString());\n   144→        }\n   145→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public static void printCollection(String message, Collection<?> c) {\n   149→        log(message);\n   150→        printCollection(c);\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    public static boolean doActionTrace() {\n   154→        return getTrace() && getActionTrace();\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    public static boolean doTrace() {\n   158→        return getTrace();\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    public static boolean doDebug() {\n   162→        return true;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public static boolean doStat() {\n   166→        return true;\n   167→    }\n   168→\n   169→    public static boolean getTrace() {\n   170→        return TradeConfig.getTrace();\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public static boolean getActionTrace() {\n   174→        return TradeConfig.getActionTrace();\n   175→    }\n   176→}\n   177→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"45bc8669-244c-42c7-afc2-c3ec3c26be9c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gb6ou35qoRKG5vGNmwWEX3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class MDBStats extends java.util.HashMap<String, TimerStat> {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3759835921094193760L;\n    27→    // Singleton class\n    28→    private static MDBStats mdbStats = null;\n    29→\n    30→    private MDBStats() {\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public static synchronized MDBStats getInstance() {\n    34→        if (mdbStats == null) {\n    35→            mdbStats = new MDBStats();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return mdbStats;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public TimerStat addTiming(String type, long sendTime, long recvTime) {\n    41→        TimerStat stats = null;\n    42→        synchronized (type) {\n    43→\n    44→            stats = get(type);\n    45→            if (stats == null) {\n    46→                stats = new TimerStat();\n    47→            }\n    48→\n    49→            long time = recvTime - sendTime;\n    50→            if (time > stats.getMax()) {\n    51→                stats.setMax(time);\n    52→            }\n    53→            if (time < stats.getMin()) {\n    54→                stats.setMin(time);\n    55→            }\n    56→            stats.setCount(stats.getCount() + 1);\n    57→            stats.setTotalTime(stats.getTotalTime() + time);\n    58→\n    59→            put(type, stats);\n    60→        }\n    61→        return stats;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public synchronized void reset() {\n    65→        clear();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"01464944-c3bd-4843-a9e9-420e0c00caf9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VTeBD9Q1qNEMLcayHCj9mr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→/** This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary WebSocket\n    32→ *  and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    33→ *  It fires a CDI event everytime a price change is added\n    34→ **/\n    35→\n    36→@ApplicationScoped\n    37→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList  {\n    38→\n    39→  private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    40→  private int maxSize = 5;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject\n    43→  @QuotePriceChange\n    44→  Event<String> quotePriceChangeEvent;\n    45→\n    46→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    47→\n    48→    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    49→\n    50→    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    51→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    52→\n    53→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    54→      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n    55→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    56→      }      \n    57→      // Fire async event without ManagedExecutorService (Quarkus handles async events differently)\n    58→      quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    59→    }\n    60→    return true;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    64→    return list.isEmpty();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Size(max=5)\n    68→  @NotEmpty\n    69→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    70→    return list;\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"3bd9a62a-1ce4-4f88-9773-9c48dce6f3ea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TYD9P8RmEDM1wraErfVrRn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class TimerStat {\n    25→\n    26→    private double min = 1000000000.0, max = 0.0, totalTime = 0.0;\n    27→    private int count;\n    28→\n    29→    /**\n    30→     * Returns the count.\n    31→     *\n    32→     * @return int\n    33→     */\n    34→    public int getCount() {\n    35→        return count;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Returns the max.\n    40→     *\n    41→     * @return double\n    42→     */\n    43→    public double getMax() {\n    44→        return max;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    /**\n    48→     * Returns the min.\n    49→     *\n    50→     * @return double\n    51→     */\n    52→    public double getMin() {\n    53→        return min;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * Sets the count.\n    58→     *\n    59→     * @param count\n    60→     *            The count to set\n    61→     */\n    62→    public void setCount(int count) {\n    63→        this.count = count;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Sets the max.\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @param max\n    70→     *            The max to set\n    71→     */\n    72→    public void setMax(double max) {\n    73→        this.max = max;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    /**\n    77→     * Sets the min.\n    78→     *\n    79→     * @param min\n    80→     *            The min to set\n    81→     */\n    82→    public void setMin(double min) {\n    83→        this.min = min;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Returns the totalTime.\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @return double\n    90→     */\n    91→    public double getTotalTime() {\n    92→        return totalTime;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    /**\n    96→     * Sets the totalTime.\n    97→     *\n    98→     * @param totalTime\n    99→     *            The totalTime to set\n   100→     */\n   101→    public void setTotalTime(double totalTime) {\n   102→        this.totalTime = totalTime;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Returns the max in Secs\n   107→     *\n   108→     * @return double\n   109→     */\n   110→    public double getMaxSecs() {\n   111→        return max / 1000.0;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    /**\n   115→     * Returns the min in Secs\n   116→     *\n   117→     * @return double\n   118→     */\n   119→    public double getMinSecs() {\n   120→        return min / 1000.0;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Returns the average time in Secs\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return double\n   127→     */\n   128→    public double getAvgSecs() {\n   129→\n   130→        double avg = getTotalTime() / getCount();\n   131→        return avg / 1000.0;\n   132→    }\n   133→}\n   134→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bxco1HSA9c3CSa498MC4m5","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"05a08872-1cb5-4da5-a1e9-b0316c765c7d"}
