{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QhNcPtv6ZK6CPUUHX9yJTr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"bb70de22-15b1-4781-872d-4f18aef6b304"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SaGknjdY1v5vdJje7vFF49","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    22→\n    23→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n    24→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\n    25→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n    26→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\n    27→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n    28→\n    29→@Qualifier\n    30→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    31→@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\n    32→public @interface TradeSession2Direct {}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"965a6d1e-cb0a-44b5-89e3-ab49cbab88c2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xinh4ENaVrxZ1xSXhJZQr8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    20→ * \n    21→ * Original: JMS TextMessage with properties (command, orderID, twoPhase, direct, publishTime)\n    22→ * Quarkus: Plain Java object (POJO) used with Reactive Messaging\n    23→ * \n    24→ * In Jakarta EE, JMS messages were heavyweight with:\n    25→ * - message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\")\n    26→ * - message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID)\n    27→ * - message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase)\n    28→ * - message.setText(...)\n    29→ * \n    30→ * In Quarkus, we use simple POJOs that are serialized automatically.\n    31→ * This is cleaner, type-safe, and doesn't require JMS infrastructure.\n    32→ */\n    33→public class OrderMessage {\n    34→    \n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_NEW_ORDER = \"neworder\";\n    36→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    37→    \n    38→    private String command;\n    39→    private Integer orderID;\n    40→    private boolean twoPhase;\n    41→    private boolean direct;\n    42→    private long publishTime;\n    43→    private String text;\n    44→    \n    45→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    46→    public OrderMessage() {\n    47→    }\n    48→    \n    49→    // Factory method for new order messages\n    50→    public static OrderMessage newOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    51→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    52→        msg.command = COMMAND_NEW_ORDER;\n    53→        msg.orderID = orderID;\n    54→        msg.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    55→        msg.direct = false;\n    56→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    57→        msg.text = \"Order message for orderID=\" + orderID;\n    58→        return msg;\n    59→    }\n    60→    \n    61→    // Factory method for ping messages\n    62→    public static OrderMessage ping(String text) {\n    63→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    64→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    65→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    66→        msg.text = text;\n    67→        return msg;\n    68→    }\n    69→    \n    70→    // Getters and setters\n    71→    public String getCommand() {\n    72→        return command;\n    73→    }\n    74→    \n    75→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    76→        this.command = command;\n    77→    }\n    78→    \n    79→    public Integer getOrderID() {\n    80→        return orderID;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setOrderID(Integer orderID) {\n    84→        this.orderID = orderID;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public boolean isTwoPhase() {\n    88→        return twoPhase;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setTwoPhase(boolean twoPhase) {\n    92→        this.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public boolean isDirect() {\n    96→        return direct;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setDirect(boolean direct) {\n   100→        this.direct = direct;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   104→        return publishTime;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   108→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public String getText() {\n   112→        return text;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setText(String text) {\n   116→        this.text = text;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    @Override\n   120→    public String toString() {\n   121→        return \"OrderMessage{\" +\n   122→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   123→                \", orderID=\" + orderID +\n   124→                \", twoPhase=\" + twoPhase +\n   125→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   126→                '}';\n   127→    }\n   128→}\n   129→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"ace52cc6-806e-4cf6-887a-73a76de7007f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014GpewuSrTpqyjnZ2EBqraL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    22→ * \n    23→ * Original: JMS TextMessage published to jms/TradeStreamerTopic\n    24→ * Properties: command, symbol, price, oldPrice, publishTime\n    25→ * \n    26→ * Quarkus: Simple POJO with same information, used with Reactive Messaging.\n    27→ * \n    28→ * The DTStreamer3MDB consumed topic messages for:\n    29→ * - \"updateQuote\" command: Log price changes\n    30→ * - \"ping\" command: Health check / performance testing\n    31→ */\n    32→public class QuoteUpdateMessage {\n    33→    \n    34→    public static final String COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE = \"updateQuote\";\n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    36→    \n    37→    private String command;\n    38→    private String symbol;\n    39→    private BigDecimal price;\n    40→    private BigDecimal oldPrice;\n    41→    private long publishTime;\n    42→    private String text;\n    43→    \n    44→    // Additional fields for full quote update (matching original JMS message properties)\n    45→    private String company;\n    46→    private BigDecimal open;\n    47→    private BigDecimal low;\n    48→    private BigDecimal high;\n    49→    private double volume;\n    50→    private BigDecimal changeFactor;\n    51→    private double sharesTraded;\n    52→    \n    53→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    54→    public QuoteUpdateMessage() {\n    55→    }\n    56→    \n    57→    // Factory method for quote update\n    58→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage quoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n    59→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    60→        msg.command = COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE;\n    61→        msg.symbol = symbol;\n    62→        msg.price = newPrice;\n    63→        msg.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n    64→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    65→        msg.text = \"Quote update for \" + symbol + \": \" + oldPrice + \" -> \" + newPrice;\n    66→        return msg;\n    67→    }\n    68→    \n    69→    // Factory method for ping\n    70→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage ping(String text) {\n    71→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    72→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    73→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    74→        msg.text = text;\n    75→        return msg;\n    76→    }\n    77→    \n    78→    // Getters and setters\n    79→    public String getCommand() {\n    80→        return command;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    84→        this.command = command;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public String getSymbol() {\n    88→        return symbol;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n    92→        this.symbol = symbol;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n    96→        return price;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   100→        this.price = price;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public BigDecimal getOldPrice() {\n   104→        return oldPrice;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setOldPrice(BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n   108→        this.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   112→        return publishTime;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   116→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    public String getText() {\n   120→        return text;\n   121→    }\n   122→    \n   123→    public void setText(String text) {\n   124→        this.text = text;\n   125→    }\n   126→    \n   127→    // Additional getters/setters for full quote update fields\n   128→    public String getCompany() {\n   129→        return company;\n   130→    }\n   131→    \n   132→    public void setCompany(String company) {\n   133→        this.company = company;\n   134→    }\n   135→    \n   136→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   137→        return open;\n   138→    }\n   139→    \n   140→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   141→        this.open = open;\n   142→    }\n   143→    \n   144→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   145→        return low;\n   146→    }\n   147→    \n   148→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   149→        this.low = low;\n   150→    }\n   151→    \n   152→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   153→        return high;\n   154→    }\n   155→    \n   156→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   157→        this.high = high;\n   158→    }\n   159→    \n   160→    public double getVolume() {\n   161→        return volume;\n   162→    }\n   163→    \n   164→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   165→        this.volume = volume;\n   166→    }\n   167→    \n   168→    public BigDecimal getChangeFactor() {\n   169→        return changeFactor;\n   170→    }\n   171→    \n   172→    public void setChangeFactor(BigDecimal changeFactor) {\n   173→        this.changeFactor = changeFactor;\n   174→    }\n   175→    \n   176→    public double getSharesTraded() {\n   177→        return sharesTraded;\n   178→    }\n   179→    \n   180→    public void setSharesTraded(double sharesTraded) {\n   181→        this.sharesTraded = sharesTraded;\n   182→    }\n   183→    \n   184→    @Override\n   185→    public String toString() {\n   186→        return \"QuoteUpdateMessage{\" +\n   187→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   188→                \", symbol='\" + symbol + '\\'' +\n   189→                \", price=\" + price +\n   190→                \", oldPrice=\" + oldPrice +\n   191→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   192→                '}';\n   193→    }\n   194→}\n   195→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"da84007b-2149-41f8-81db-92c459d7c37a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UCXtEfJyLvBnaHBwxZ44D1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * MIGRATION NOTE: Updated to use RoundingMode enum instead of deprecated BigDecimal constants.\n    26→ */\n    27→public class FinancialUtils {\n    28→\n    29→    public static final RoundingMode ROUND = RoundingMode.HALF_UP;\n    30→    public static final int SCALE = 2;\n    31→    public static final BigDecimal ZERO = new BigDecimal(\"0.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    32→    public static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(\"1.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    33→    public static final BigDecimal HUNDRED = new BigDecimal(\"100.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    34→\n    35→    public static BigDecimal computeGain(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    36→        return currentBalance.subtract(openBalance).setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static BigDecimal computeGainPercent(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    40→        if (openBalance.doubleValue() == 0.0) {\n    41→            return ZERO;\n    42→        }\n    43→        BigDecimal gainPercent = currentBalance.divide(openBalance, SCALE, ROUND)\n    44→                .subtract(ONE)\n    45→                .multiply(HUNDRED);\n    46→        return gainPercent;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static BigDecimal computeHoldingsTotal(Collection<?> holdingDataBeans) {\n    50→        BigDecimal holdingsTotal = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    51→        if (holdingDataBeans == null) {\n    52→            return holdingsTotal;\n    53→        }\n    54→        for (Object obj : holdingDataBeans) {\n    55→            HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) obj;\n    56→            BigDecimal total = holdingData.getPurchasePrice()\n    57→                    .multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    58→            holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal.add(total);\n    59→        }\n    60→        return holdingsTotal.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public static String printGainHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    64→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    65→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    66→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    67→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    68→        } else {\n    69→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    70→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    71→        }\n    72→\n    73→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND) + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    74→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    75→        return htmlString;\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public static String printChangeHTML(double change) {\n    79→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    80→        if (change < 0.0) {\n    81→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    82→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    83→        } else {\n    84→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    85→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    86→        }\n    87→\n    88→        htmlString += change + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    89→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    90→        return htmlString;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public static String printGainPercentHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    94→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    95→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    96→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    97→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    98→        } else {\n    99→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">+\";\n   100→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n   101→        }\n   102→\n   103→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n   104→        htmlString += \"%</FONT></B>)<IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n   105→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n   106→        return htmlString;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public static String printQuoteLink(String symbol) {\n   110→        return \"<A href=\\\"app?action=quotes&symbols=\" + symbol + \"\\\">\" + symbol + \"</A>\";\n   111→    }\n   112→}\n   113→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"1cd2b27a-6f49-4419-84a1-a91599fd67fa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0141YC5bvsyqkGBqTBmJ47zw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.AbstractSequentialList;\n    19→import java.util.ListIterator;\n    20→\n    21→public class KeyBlock extends AbstractSequentialList<Object> {\n    22→\n    23→    // min and max provide range of valid primary keys for this KeyBlock\n    24→    private int min = 0;\n    25→    private int max = 0;\n    26→    private int index = 0;\n    27→\n    28→    /**\n    29→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    30→     */\n    31→    public KeyBlock() {\n    32→        super();\n    33→        min = 0;\n    34→        max = 0;\n    35→        index = min;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    40→     */\n    41→    public KeyBlock(int min, int max) {\n    42→        super();\n    43→        this.min = min;\n    44→        this.max = max;\n    45→        index = min;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    /**\n    49→     * @see AbstractCollection#size()\n    50→     */\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public int size() {\n    53→        return (max - min) + 1;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * @see AbstractSequentialList#listIterator(int)\n    58→     */\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public ListIterator<Object> listIterator(int arg0) {\n    61→        return new KeyBlockIterator();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    class KeyBlockIterator implements ListIterator<Object> {\n    65→\n    66→        /**\n    67→         * @see ListIterator#hasNext()\n    68→         */\n    69→        @Override\n    70→        public boolean hasNext() {\n    71→            return index <= max;\n    72→        }\n    73→\n    74→        /**\n    75→         * @see ListIterator#next()\n    76→         */\n    77→        @Override\n    78→        public synchronized Object next() {\n    79→            if (index > max) {\n    80→                throw new java.lang.RuntimeException(\"KeyBlock:next() -- Error KeyBlock depleted\");\n    81→            }\n    82→            return new Integer(index++);\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        /**\n    86→         * @see ListIterator#hasPrevious()\n    87→         */\n    88→        @Override\n    89→        public boolean hasPrevious() {\n    90→            return index > min;\n    91→        }\n    92→\n    93→        /**\n    94→         * @see ListIterator#previous()\n    95→         */\n    96→        @Override\n    97→        public Object previous() {\n    98→            return new Integer(--index);\n    99→        }\n   100→\n   101→        /**\n   102→         * @see ListIterator#nextIndex()\n   103→         */\n   104→        @Override\n   105→        public int nextIndex() {\n   106→            return index - min;\n   107→        }\n   108→\n   109→        /**\n   110→         * @see ListIterator#previousIndex()\n   111→         */\n   112→        @Override\n   113→        public int previousIndex() {\n   114→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: previousIndex() not supported\");\n   115→        }\n   116→\n   117→        /**\n   118→         * @see ListIterator#add()\n   119→         */\n   120→        @Override\n   121→        public void add(Object o) {\n   122→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: add() not supported\");\n   123→        }\n   124→\n   125→        /**\n   126→         * @see ListIterator#remove()\n   127→         */\n   128→        @Override\n   129→        public void remove() {\n   130→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: remove() not supported\");\n   131→        }\n   132→\n   133→        /**\n   134→         * @see ListIterator#set(Object)\n   135→         */\n   136→        @Override\n   137→        public void set(Object arg0) {\n   138→        }\n   139→    }\n   140→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"2fcbc0ba-b305-483f-8916-ff4c0967159c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014pVdwoa4mf5BCggXAevSk1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collection;\n    19→import java.util.Iterator;\n    20→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    21→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    22→\n    23→/**\n    24→ * MIGRATION NOTE: This class remains largely unchanged.\n    25→ * In Quarkus, you could also use JBoss Logging or SLF4J.\n    26→ * Quarkus uses JBoss LogManager by default.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class Log {\n    29→\n    30→    private final static Logger log = Logger.getLogger(\"daytrader\");\n    31→\n    32→    public static void log(String message) {\n    33→        log.log(Level.INFO, message);\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2) {\n    37→        log(msg1 + msg2);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    41→        log(msg1 + msg2 + msg3);\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public static void error(String message) {\n    45→        message = \"Error: \" + message;\n    46→        log.severe(message);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static void error(String message, Throwable e) {\n    50→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\" + e.toString());\n    51→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, Throwable e) {\n    55→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3, Throwable e) {\n    59→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public static void error(Throwable e, String message) {\n    63→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    64→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2) {\n    68→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    72→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public static void trace(String message) {\n    76→        log.log(Level.FINE, message + \" threadID=\" + Thread.currentThread());\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    public static void traceInterceptor(String message, Object parm1) {\n    80→        log.log(Level.SEVERE, message, parm1);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1) {\n    84→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \")\");\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2) {\n    88→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \")\");\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3) {\n    92→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \")\");\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4) {\n    96→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \")\");\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5) {\n   100→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \")\");\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6) {\n   104→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \")\");\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6, Object parm7) {\n   108→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \", \" + parm7 + \")\");\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public static void traceEnter(String message) {\n   112→        log.entering(\"Log\", message);\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public static void traceExit(String message) {\n   116→        log.exiting(\"Log\", message);\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public static void stat(String message) {\n   120→        log(message);\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public static void debug(String message) {\n   124→        log.log(Level.FINE, message);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public static void print(String message) {\n   128→        log(message);\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public static void printObject(Object o) {\n   132→        log(\"\\t\" + o.toString());\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n   136→    public static void printCollection(Collection c) {\n   137→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   138→        if (c == null) {\n   139→            return;\n   140→        }\n   141→        Iterator it = c.iterator();\n   142→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   143→            log(\"\\t\\t\" + it.next().toString());\n   144→        }\n   145→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public static void printCollection(String message, Collection<?> c) {\n   149→        log(message);\n   150→        printCollection(c);\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    public static boolean doActionTrace() {\n   154→        return getTrace() && getActionTrace();\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    public static boolean doTrace() {\n   158→        return getTrace();\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    public static boolean doDebug() {\n   162→        return true;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public static boolean doStat() {\n   166→        return true;\n   167→    }\n   168→\n   169→    public static boolean getTrace() {\n   170→        return TradeConfig.getTrace();\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public static boolean getActionTrace() {\n   174→        return TradeConfig.getActionTrace();\n   175→    }\n   176→}\n   177→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"096e8334-441f-4faf-a8fa-3043f9632b76"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KNboqVbf8u22V6Cjye1HQ4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class MDBStats extends java.util.HashMap<String, TimerStat> {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3759835921094193760L;\n    27→    // Singleton class\n    28→    private static MDBStats mdbStats = null;\n    29→\n    30→    private MDBStats() {\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public static synchronized MDBStats getInstance() {\n    34→        if (mdbStats == null) {\n    35→            mdbStats = new MDBStats();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return mdbStats;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public TimerStat addTiming(String type, long sendTime, long recvTime) {\n    41→        TimerStat stats = null;\n    42→        synchronized (type) {\n    43→\n    44→            stats = get(type);\n    45→            if (stats == null) {\n    46→                stats = new TimerStat();\n    47→            }\n    48→\n    49→            long time = recvTime - sendTime;\n    50→            if (time > stats.getMax()) {\n    51→                stats.setMax(time);\n    52→            }\n    53→            if (time < stats.getMin()) {\n    54→                stats.setMin(time);\n    55→            }\n    56→            stats.setCount(stats.getCount() + 1);\n    57→            stats.setTotalTime(stats.getTotalTime() + time);\n    58→\n    59→            put(type, stats);\n    60→        }\n    61→        return stats;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public synchronized void reset() {\n    65→        clear();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"8b418ce9-ddfe-4be8-85eb-288e6b559244"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PiQKdkeUUsEYuVVj4nru5V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→/** This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary WebSocket\n    32→ *  and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    33→ *  It fires a CDI event everytime a price change is added\n    34→ **/\n    35→\n    36→@ApplicationScoped\n    37→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList  {\n    38→\n    39→  private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    40→  private int maxSize = 5;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject\n    43→  @QuotePriceChange\n    44→  Event<String> quotePriceChangeEvent;\n    45→\n    46→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    47→\n    48→    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    49→\n    50→    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    51→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    52→\n    53→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    54→      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n    55→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    56→      }      \n    57→      // Fire async event without ManagedExecutorService (Quarkus handles async events differently)\n    58→      quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    59→    }\n    60→    return true;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    64→    return list.isEmpty();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Size(max=5)\n    68→  @NotEmpty\n    69→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    70→    return list;\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"a988f518-4acf-4dd6-b112-7df40c0021f6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XNWJpyFxUoS1QGKjKQvvUt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class TimerStat {\n    25→\n    26→    private double min = 1000000000.0, max = 0.0, totalTime = 0.0;\n    27→    private int count;\n    28→\n    29→    /**\n    30→     * Returns the count.\n    31→     *\n    32→     * @return int\n    33→     */\n    34→    public int getCount() {\n    35→        return count;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Returns the max.\n    40→     *\n    41→     * @return double\n    42→     */\n    43→    public double getMax() {\n    44→        return max;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    /**\n    48→     * Returns the min.\n    49→     *\n    50→     * @return double\n    51→     */\n    52→    public double getMin() {\n    53→        return min;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * Sets the count.\n    58→     *\n    59→     * @param count\n    60→     *            The count to set\n    61→     */\n    62→    public void setCount(int count) {\n    63→        this.count = count;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Sets the max.\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @param max\n    70→     *            The max to set\n    71→     */\n    72→    public void setMax(double max) {\n    73→        this.max = max;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    /**\n    77→     * Sets the min.\n    78→     *\n    79→     * @param min\n    80→     *            The min to set\n    81→     */\n    82→    public void setMin(double min) {\n    83→        this.min = min;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Returns the totalTime.\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @return double\n    90→     */\n    91→    public double getTotalTime() {\n    92→        return totalTime;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    /**\n    96→     * Sets the totalTime.\n    97→     *\n    98→     * @param totalTime\n    99→     *            The totalTime to set\n   100→     */\n   101→    public void setTotalTime(double totalTime) {\n   102→        this.totalTime = totalTime;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Returns the max in Secs\n   107→     *\n   108→     * @return double\n   109→     */\n   110→    public double getMaxSecs() {\n   111→        return max / 1000.0;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    /**\n   115→     * Returns the min in Secs\n   116→     *\n   117→     * @return double\n   118→     */\n   119→    public double getMinSecs() {\n   120→        return min / 1000.0;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Returns the average time in Secs\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return double\n   127→     */\n   128→    public double getAvgSecs() {\n   129→\n   130→        double avg = getTotalTime() / getCount();\n   131→        return avg / 1000.0;\n   132→    }\n   133→}\n   134→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"01e9f3d8-0560-45a5-a315-c0ffa746970d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VqdsW3k9QRzJ5KTVxVKKvS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.Random;\n    22→\n    23→/**\n    24→ * TradeConfig is a JavaBean holding all configuration and runtime parameters\n    25→ * for the Trade application.\n    26→ * \n    27→ * MIGRATION NOTE: In Quarkus, configuration should ideally be externalized to\n    28→ * application.properties and injected via @ConfigProperty. This class is\n    29→ * simplified for migration purposes.\n    30→ */\n    31→public class TradeConfig {\n    32→\n    33→    /* Trade Runtime Mode parameters */\n    34→    // Support original Jakarta runtime modes for compatibility\n    35→    private static String[] runTimeModeNames = { \"Direct (JPA)\", \"Direct (JDBC)\", \"Full EJB3\", \"Session to Direct\" };\n    36→    public static final int DIRECT_JPA = 0;\n    37→    public static final int DIRECT_JDBC = 1;\n    38→    public static final int DIRECT = DIRECT_JDBC;  // Alias for TradeDirect\n    39→    public static final int EJB3 = 2;\n    40→    public static final int SESSION_TO_DIRECT = 3;\n    41→    private static int runTimeMode = DIRECT_JPA;\n    42→\n    43→    private static String[] orderProcessingModeNames = { \"Sync\", \"Async\", \"Async 2-Phase\" };\n    44→    public static final int SYNCH = 0;\n    45→    public static final int ASYNCH = 1;\n    46→    public static final int ASYNCH_2PHASE = 2;  // Two-phase commit mode\n    47→    private static int orderProcessingMode = SYNCH;\n    48→    \n    49→    // Quote price change publishing flag\n    50→    private static boolean publishQuotePriceChange = true;\n    51→\n    52→    /* Trade Database Scaling parameters */\n    53→    private static int MAX_USERS = 200;\n    54→    private static int MAX_QUOTES = 400;\n    55→\n    56→    /* Trade Config Miscellaneous items */\n    57→    public static int KEYBLOCKSIZE = 1000;\n    58→    public static int QUOTES_PER_PAGE = 10;\n    59→    public static boolean RND_USER = true;\n    60→    private static int MAX_HOLDINGS = 10;\n    61→    private static int count = 0;\n    62→    private static Object userID_count_semaphore = new Object();\n    63→    private static int userID_count = 0;\n    64→    private static String hostName = null;\n    65→    private static Random r0 = new Random(System.currentTimeMillis());\n    66→    private static Random randomNumberGenerator = r0;\n    67→    public static final String newUserPrefix = \"ru:\";\n    68→    public static final int verifyPercent = 5;\n    69→    private static boolean updateQuotePrices = true;\n    70→    private static int primIterations = 1;\n    71→    private static boolean longRun = true;\n    72→    private static boolean displayOrderAlerts = true;\n    73→    private static int marketSummaryInterval = 20;\n    74→    private static boolean trace = false;\n    75→    private static boolean actionTrace = false;\n    76→    private static int listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = 100;\n    77→\n    78→    // Penny stock handling\n    79→    public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_PRICE;\n    80→    public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER;\n    81→    public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE;\n    82→    public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER;\n    83→    \n    84→    static {\n    85→        PENNY_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(\"0.01\").setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n    86→        PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(\"600.0\").setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n    87→        MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(\"400\").setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n    88→        MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(\"0.5\").setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    /* Trade Scenario actions */\n    92→    public static final int HOME_OP = 0;\n    93→    public static final int QUOTE_OP = 1;\n    94→    public static final int LOGIN_OP = 2;\n    95→    public static final int LOGOUT_OP = 3;\n    96→    public static final int REGISTER_OP = 4;\n    97→    public static final int ACCOUNT_OP = 5;\n    98→    public static final int PORTFOLIO_OP = 6;\n    99→    public static final int BUY_OP = 7;\n   100→    public static final int SELL_OP = 8;\n   101→    public static final int UPDATEACCOUNT_OP = 9;\n   102→\n   103→    private static int[][] scenarioMixes = {\n   104→        { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 10, 12, 4, 4, 4 }, // STANDARD\n   105→        { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 7, 7, 7, 7, 6 },   // High Volume\n   106→    };\n   107→    private static char[] actions = { 'h', 'q', 'l', 'o', 'r', 'a', 'p', 'b', 's', 'u' };\n   108→    private static int sellDeficit = 0;\n   109→    private static int scenarioCount = 0;\n   110→\n   111→    // Card deck for user selection\n   112→    private static ArrayList<Integer> deck = null;\n   113→    private static int card = 0;\n   114→\n   115→    private static final BigDecimal orderFee = new BigDecimal(\"24.95\");\n   116→    private static final BigDecimal cashFee = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\");\n   117→    private static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(1.0);\n   118→\n   119→    // Hostname\n   120→    private static String getHostname() {\n   121→        try {\n   122→            if (hostName == null) {\n   123→                hostName = java.net.InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName();\n   124→                try {\n   125→                    hostName = hostName.substring(0, hostName.indexOf('.'));\n   126→                } catch (Exception e) {\n   127→                    // ignore\n   128→                }\n   129→            }\n   130→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   131→            Log.error(\"Exception getting local host name using 'localhost' - \", e);\n   132→            hostName = \"localhost\";\n   133→        }\n   134→        return hostName;\n   135→    }\n   136→\n   137→    public static String[] getRunTimeModeNames() {\n   138→        return runTimeModeNames;\n   139→    }\n   140→\n   141→    public static char getScenarioAction(boolean newUser) {\n   142→        int r = rndInt(100);\n   143→        int i = 0;\n   144→        int sum = scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   145→        while (sum <= r) {\n   146→            i++;\n   147→            sum += scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   148→        }\n   149→        incrementScenarioCount();\n   150→\n   151→        if ((!newUser) && (actions[i] == 'b')) {\n   152→            synchronized (TradeConfig.class) {\n   153→                if (sellDeficit > 0) {\n   154→                    sellDeficit--;\n   155→                    return 's';\n   156→                }\n   157→            }\n   158→        }\n   159→        return actions[i];\n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public static String getUserID() {\n   163→        return RND_USER ? rndUserID() : nextUserID();\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public static BigDecimal getOrderFee(String orderType) {\n   167→        if (\"BUY\".equalsIgnoreCase(orderType) || \"SELL\".equalsIgnoreCase(orderType)) {\n   168→            return orderFee;\n   169→        }\n   170→        return cashFee;\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public static synchronized void incrementSellDeficit() {\n   174→        sellDeficit++;\n   175→    }\n   176→\n   177→    public static String nextUserID() {\n   178→        String userID;\n   179→        synchronized (userID_count_semaphore) {\n   180→            userID = \"uid:\" + userID_count;\n   181→            userID_count++;\n   182→            if (userID_count % MAX_USERS == 0) {\n   183→                userID_count = 0;\n   184→            }\n   185→        }\n   186→        return userID;\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    public static double random() {\n   190→        return randomNumberGenerator.nextDouble();\n   191→    }\n   192→\n   193→    public static String rndAddress() {\n   194→        return rndInt(1000) + \" Oak St.\";\n   195→    }\n   196→\n   197→    public static String rndBalance() {\n   198→        return \"1000000\";\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    public static String rndCreditCard() {\n   202→        return rndInt(100) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000);\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    public static String rndEmail(String userID) {\n   206→        return userID.replace(\":\", \"\") + \"@\" + rndInt(100) + \".com\";\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    public static String rndFullName() {\n   210→        return \"first:\" + rndInt(1000) + \" last:\" + rndInt(5000);\n   211→    }\n   212→\n   213→    public static int rndInt(int i) {\n   214→        return (int) (random() * i);\n   215→    }\n   216→\n   217→    public static float rndFloat(int i) {\n   218→        return (float) (random() * i);\n   219→    }\n   220→\n   221→    public static BigDecimal rndBigDecimal(float f) {\n   222→        return new BigDecimal(random() * f).setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n   223→    }\n   224→\n   225→    public static boolean rndBoolean() {\n   226→        return randomNumberGenerator.nextBoolean();\n   227→    }\n   228→\n   229→    public static synchronized String rndNewUserID() {\n   230→        return newUserPrefix + getHostname() + System.currentTimeMillis() + count++;\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    public static float rndPrice() {\n   234→        return rndInt(200) + 1.0f;\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    public static BigDecimal getRandomPriceChangeFactor() {\n   238→        double percentGain = rndFloat(1) * 0.1;\n   239→        if (random() < .5) {\n   240→            percentGain *= -1;\n   241→        }\n   242→        percentGain += 1;\n   243→\n   244→        BigDecimal percentGainBD = new BigDecimal(percentGain).setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n   245→        if (percentGainBD.doubleValue() <= 0.0) {\n   246→            percentGainBD = ONE;\n   247→        }\n   248→        return percentGainBD;\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    public static float rndQuantity() {\n   252→        return rndInt(200) + 1.0f;\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public static String rndSymbol() {\n   256→        return \"s:\" + rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1);\n   257→    }\n   258→\n   259→    public static String rndSymbols() {\n   260→        StringBuilder symbols = new StringBuilder();\n   261→        int num_symbols = rndInt(QUOTES_PER_PAGE);\n   262→\n   263→        for (int i = 0; i <= num_symbols; i++) {\n   264→            symbols.append(\"s:\").append(rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1));\n   265→            if (i < num_symbols) {\n   266→                symbols.append(\",\");\n   267→            }\n   268→        }\n   269→        return symbols.toString();\n   270→    }\n   271→\n   272→    public static String rndUserID() {\n   273→        return getNextUserIDFromDeck();\n   274→    }\n   275→\n   276→    private static synchronized String getNextUserIDFromDeck() {\n   277→        int numUsers = getMAX_USERS();\n   278→        if (deck == null) {\n   279→            deck = new ArrayList<>(numUsers);\n   280→            for (int i = 0; i < numUsers; i++) {\n   281→                deck.add(i);\n   282→            }\n   283→            java.util.Collections.shuffle(deck, r0);\n   284→        }\n   285→        if (card >= numUsers) {\n   286→            card = 0;\n   287→        }\n   288→        return \"uid:\" + deck.get(card++);\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    // Getters and Setters\n   292→    public static String[] getOrderProcessingModeNames() {\n   293→        return orderProcessingModeNames;\n   294→    }\n   295→\n   296→    public static int[][] getScenarioMixes() {\n   297→        return scenarioMixes;\n   298→    }\n   299→\n   300→    public static int getMAX_USERS() {\n   301→        return MAX_USERS;\n   302→    }\n   303→\n   304→    public static void setMAX_USERS(int maxUsers) {\n   305→        MAX_USERS = maxUsers;\n   306→        deck = null;\n   307→    }\n   308→\n   309→    public static int getMAX_QUOTES() {\n   310→        return MAX_QUOTES;\n   311→    }\n   312→\n   313→    public static void setMAX_QUOTES(int maxQuotes) {\n   314→        MAX_QUOTES = maxQuotes;\n   315→    }\n   316→\n   317→    public static int getMAX_HOLDINGS() {\n   318→        return MAX_HOLDINGS;\n   319→    }\n   320→\n   321→    public static void setMAX_HOLDINGS(int maxHoldings) {\n   322→        MAX_HOLDINGS = maxHoldings;\n   323→    }\n   324→\n   325→    public static int getScenarioCount() {\n   326→        return scenarioCount;\n   327→    }\n   328→\n   329→    public static void setScenarioCount(int count) {\n   330→        scenarioCount = count;\n   331→    }\n   332→\n   333→    public static synchronized void incrementScenarioCount() {\n   334→        scenarioCount++;\n   335→    }\n   336→\n   337→    public static boolean getUpdateQuotePrices() {\n   338→        return updateQuotePrices;\n   339→    }\n   340→\n   341→    public static void setUpdateQuotePrices(boolean update) {\n   342→        updateQuotePrices = update;\n   343→    }\n   344→\n   345→    public static boolean getPublishQuotePriceChange() {\n   346→        return publishQuotePriceChange;\n   347→    }\n   348→\n   349→    public static void setPublishQuotePriceChange(boolean publish) {\n   350→        publishQuotePriceChange = publish;\n   351→    }\n   352→\n   353→    public static int getPrimIterations() {\n   354→        return primIterations;\n   355→    }\n   356→\n   357→    public static void setPrimIterations(int iter) {\n   358→        primIterations = iter;\n   359→    }\n   360→\n   361→    public static boolean getLongRun() {\n   362→        return longRun;\n   363→    }\n   364→\n   365→    public static void setLongRun(boolean run) {\n   366→        longRun = run;\n   367→    }\n   368→\n   369→    public static void setMarketSummaryInterval(int seconds) {\n   370→        marketSummaryInterval = seconds;\n   371→    }\n   372→\n   373→    public static int getMarketSummaryInterval() {\n   374→        return marketSummaryInterval;\n   375→    }\n   376→\n   377→    public static void setRunTimeMode(int value) {\n   378→        runTimeMode = value;\n   379→    }\n   380→\n   381→    public static int getRunTimeMode() {\n   382→        return runTimeMode;\n   383→    }\n   384→\n   385→    public static void setOrderProcessingMode(int value) {\n   386→        orderProcessingMode = value;\n   387→    }\n   388→\n   389→    public static int getOrderProcessingMode() {\n   390→        return orderProcessingMode;\n   391→    }\n   392→\n   393→    public static void setDisplayOrderAlerts(boolean value) {\n   394→        displayOrderAlerts = value;\n   395→    }\n   396→\n   397→    public static boolean getDisplayOrderAlerts() {\n   398→        return displayOrderAlerts;\n   399→    }\n   400→\n   401→    public static boolean getTrace() {\n   402→        return trace;\n   403→    }\n   404→\n   405→    public static void setTrace(boolean value) {\n   406→        trace = value;\n   407→    }\n   408→\n   409→    public static boolean getActionTrace() {\n   410→        return actionTrace;\n   411→    }\n   412→\n   413→    public static void setActionTrace(boolean value) {\n   414→        actionTrace = value;\n   415→    }\n   416→\n   417→    public static int getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() {\n   418→        return listQuotePriceChangeFrequency;\n   419→    }\n   420→\n   421→    public static void setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(int value) {\n   422→        listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = value;\n   423→    }\n   424→}\n   425→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"cbb4b441-cb08-462a-ae0e-333f9b5d678d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DD8HnQexHnUDsndRj7AEA9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral;\n    19→\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    21→\n    22→public class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral extends AnnotationLiteral<RuntimeMode> implements RuntimeMode {\n    23→  \n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -252789556335033400L;\n    25→    private String value;\n    26→    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n    27→        this.value = value;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @Override\n    31→    public String value() {\n    32→         return value;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"0055c809-ba01-49fc-9aa6-aad600419935"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WhEUrHqed1DCMxTazMMxNT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    29→\n    30→/**\n    31→ * MIGRATION NOTE: Removed javax.json dependency as it's not commonly used in Quarkus.\n    32→ * Use Jackson (which Quarkus uses by default) for JSON serialization instead.\n    33→ */\n    34→public class MarketSummaryDataBean implements Serializable {\n    35→\n    36→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 650652242288745600L;\n    37→    \n    38→    private BigDecimal TSIA;           /* Trade Stock Index Average */\n    39→    private BigDecimal openTSIA;       /* Trade Stock Index Average at the open */\n    40→    private double volume;             /* volume of shares traded */\n    41→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers;  /* Collection of top gaining stocks */\n    42→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers;   /* Collection of top losing stocks */\n    43→    private Date summaryDate;          /* Date this summary was taken */\n    44→    private BigDecimal gainPercent = null;\n    45→\n    46→    public MarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public MarketSummaryDataBean(BigDecimal TSIA, BigDecimal openTSIA, double volume, \n    50→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n    51→        setTSIA(TSIA);\n    52→        setOpenTSIA(openTSIA);\n    53→        setVolume(volume);\n    54→        setTopGainers(topGainers);\n    55→        setTopLosers(topLosers);\n    56→        setSummaryDate(new java.sql.Date(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n    57→        gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    public static MarketSummaryDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    61→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> gain = new ArrayList<>();\n    62→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> lose = new ArrayList<>();\n    63→\n    64→        for (int ii = 0; ii < 5; ii++) {\n    65→            QuoteDataBean quote1 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    66→            QuoteDataBean quote2 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    67→            gain.add(quote1);\n    68→            lose.add(quote2);\n    69→        }\n    70→\n    71→        return new MarketSummaryDataBean(\n    72→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), \n    73→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), \n    74→            TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), \n    75→            gain, \n    76→            lose\n    77→        );\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @Override\n    81→    public String toString() {\n    82→        String ret = \"\\n\\tMarket Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() \n    83→            + \"\\n\\t\\t        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() \n    84→            + \"\\n\\t\\t    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA()\n    85→            + \"\\n\\t\\t        gain:\" + getGainPercent() \n    86→            + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume:\" + getVolume();\n    87→\n    88→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n    89→            return ret;\n    90→        }\n    91→        \n    92→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Gainers:\";\n    93→        for (QuoteDataBean quoteData : getTopGainers()) {\n    94→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n    95→        }\n    96→        \n    97→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Losers:\";\n    98→        for (QuoteDataBean quoteData : getTopLosers()) {\n    99→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n   100→        }\n   101→        return ret;\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    public String toHTML() {\n   105→        String ret = \"<BR>Market Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() \n   106→            + \"<LI>        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"</LI>\" \n   107→            + \"<LI>    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA() + \"</LI>\"\n   108→            + \"<LI>      volume:\" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\";\n   109→            \n   110→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n   111→            return ret;\n   112→        }\n   113→        \n   114→        ret += \"<BR> Current Top Gainers:\";\n   115→        for (QuoteDataBean quoteData : getTopGainers()) {\n   116→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   117→        }\n   118→        \n   119→        ret += \"<BR>   Current Top Losers:\";\n   120→        for (QuoteDataBean quoteData : getTopLosers()) {\n   121→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   122→        }\n   123→        return ret;\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    public void print() {\n   127→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    // Getters and Setters\n   131→    public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   132→        if (gainPercent == null) {\n   133→            gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n   134→        }\n   135→        return gainPercent;\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public BigDecimal getTSIA() {\n   139→        return TSIA;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    public void setTSIA(BigDecimal tSIA) {\n   143→        TSIA = tSIA;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public BigDecimal getOpenTSIA() {\n   147→        return openTSIA;\n   148→    }\n   149→\n   150→    public void setOpenTSIA(BigDecimal openTSIA) {\n   151→        this.openTSIA = openTSIA;\n   152→    }\n   153→\n   154→    public double getVolume() {\n   155→        return volume;\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   159→        this.volume = volume;\n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopGainers() {\n   163→        return topGainers;\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public void setTopGainers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers) {\n   167→        this.topGainers = topGainers;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopLosers() {\n   171→        return topLosers;\n   172→    }\n   173→\n   174→    public void setTopLosers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n   175→        this.topLosers = topLosers;\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→    public Date getSummaryDate() {\n   179→        return summaryDate;\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→    public void setSummaryDate(Date summaryDate) {\n   183→        this.summaryDate = summaryDate;\n   184→    }\n   185→}\n   186→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"96b791ab-7986-49f5-b472-3908f20bcbd5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014JtKLCWhTZ4nrsnJME9oJK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→\n    20→public class RunStatsDataBean implements Serializable {\n    21→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 4017778674103242167L;\n    22→\n    23→    // Constructors\n    24→    public RunStatsDataBean() {\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    // count of trade users in the database (users w/ userID like 'uid:%')\n    28→    private int tradeUserCount;\n    29→    // count of trade stocks in the database (stocks w/ symbol like 's:%')\n    30→    private int tradeStockCount;\n    31→\n    32→    // count of new registered users in this run (users w/ userID like 'ru:%')\n    33→    // -- random user\n    34→    private int newUserCount;\n    35→\n    36→    // sum of logins by trade users\n    37→    private int sumLoginCount;\n    38→    // sum of logouts by trade users\n    39→    private int sumLogoutCount;\n    40→\n    41→    // count of holdings of trade users\n    42→    private int holdingCount;\n    43→\n    44→    // count of orders of trade users\n    45→    private int orderCount;\n    46→    // count of buy orders of trade users\n    47→    private int buyOrderCount;\n    48→    // count of sell orders of trade users\n    49→    private int sellOrderCount;\n    50→    // count of cancelled orders of trade users\n    51→    private int cancelledOrderCount;\n    52→    // count of open orders of trade users\n    53→    private int openOrderCount;\n    54→    // count of orders deleted during this trade Reset\n    55→    private int deletedOrderCount;\n    56→\n    57→    @Override\n    58→    public String toString() {\n    59→        return \"\\n\\tRunStatsData for reset at \" + new java.util.Date() + \"\\n\\t\\t      tradeUserCount: \" + getTradeUserCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t        newUserCount: \"\n    60→                + getNewUserCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t       sumLoginCount: \" + getSumLoginCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t      sumLogoutCount: \" + getSumLogoutCount()\n    61→                + \"\\n\\t\\t        holdingCount: \" + getHoldingCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t          orderCount: \" + getOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t       buyOrderCount: \"\n    62→                + getBuyOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t      sellOrderCount: \" + getSellOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t cancelledOrderCount: \" + getCancelledOrderCount()\n    63→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      openOrderCount: \" + getOpenOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t   deletedOrderCount: \" + getDeletedOrderCount();\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Gets the tradeUserCount\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @return Returns a int\n    70→     */\n    71→    public int getTradeUserCount() {\n    72→        return tradeUserCount;\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    /**\n    76→     * Sets the tradeUserCount\n    77→     *\n    78→     * @param tradeUserCount\n    79→     *            The tradeUserCount to set\n    80→     */\n    81→    public void setTradeUserCount(int tradeUserCount) {\n    82→        this.tradeUserCount = tradeUserCount;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    /**\n    86→     * Gets the newUserCount\n    87→     *\n    88→     * @return Returns a int\n    89→     */\n    90→    public int getNewUserCount() {\n    91→        return newUserCount;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    /**\n    95→     * Sets the newUserCount\n    96→     *\n    97→     * @param newUserCount\n    98→     *            The newUserCount to set\n    99→     */\n   100→    public void setNewUserCount(int newUserCount) {\n   101→        this.newUserCount = newUserCount;\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * Gets the sumLoginCount\n   106→     *\n   107→     * @return Returns a int\n   108→     */\n   109→    public int getSumLoginCount() {\n   110→        return sumLoginCount;\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * Sets the sumLoginCount\n   115→     *\n   116→     * @param sumLoginCount\n   117→     *            The sumLoginCount to set\n   118→     */\n   119→    public void setSumLoginCount(int sumLoginCount) {\n   120→        this.sumLoginCount = sumLoginCount;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Gets the sumLogoutCount\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return Returns a int\n   127→     */\n   128→    public int getSumLogoutCount() {\n   129→        return sumLogoutCount;\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    /**\n   133→     * Sets the sumLogoutCount\n   134→     *\n   135→     * @param sumLogoutCount\n   136→     *            The sumLogoutCount to set\n   137→     */\n   138→    public void setSumLogoutCount(int sumLogoutCount) {\n   139→        this.sumLogoutCount = sumLogoutCount;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    /**\n   143→     * Gets the holdingCount\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @return Returns a int\n   146→     */\n   147→    public int getHoldingCount() {\n   148→        return holdingCount;\n   149→    }\n   150→\n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Sets the holdingCount\n   153→     *\n   154→     * @param holdingCount\n   155→     *            The holdingCount to set\n   156→     */\n   157→    public void setHoldingCount(int holdingCount) {\n   158→        this.holdingCount = holdingCount;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    /**\n   162→     * Gets the buyOrderCount\n   163→     *\n   164→     * @return Returns a int\n   165→     */\n   166→    public int getBuyOrderCount() {\n   167→        return buyOrderCount;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    /**\n   171→     * Sets the buyOrderCount\n   172→     *\n   173→     * @param buyOrderCount\n   174→     *            The buyOrderCount to set\n   175→     */\n   176→    public void setBuyOrderCount(int buyOrderCount) {\n   177→        this.buyOrderCount = buyOrderCount;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    /**\n   181→     * Gets the sellOrderCount\n   182→     *\n   183→     * @return Returns a int\n   184→     */\n   185→    public int getSellOrderCount() {\n   186→        return sellOrderCount;\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    /**\n   190→     * Sets the sellOrderCount\n   191→     *\n   192→     * @param sellOrderCount\n   193→     *            The sellOrderCount to set\n   194→     */\n   195→    public void setSellOrderCount(int sellOrderCount) {\n   196→        this.sellOrderCount = sellOrderCount;\n   197→    }\n   198→\n   199→    /**\n   200→     * Gets the cancelledOrderCount\n   201→     *\n   202→     * @return Returns a int\n   203→     */\n   204→    public int getCancelledOrderCount() {\n   205→        return cancelledOrderCount;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    /**\n   209→     * Sets the cancelledOrderCount\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param cancelledOrderCount\n   212→     *            The cancelledOrderCount to set\n   213→     */\n   214→    public void setCancelledOrderCount(int cancelledOrderCount) {\n   215→        this.cancelledOrderCount = cancelledOrderCount;\n   216→    }\n   217→\n   218→    /**\n   219→     * Gets the openOrderCount\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return Returns a int\n   222→     */\n   223→    public int getOpenOrderCount() {\n   224→        return openOrderCount;\n   225→    }\n   226→\n   227→    /**\n   228→     * Sets the openOrderCount\n   229→     *\n   230→     * @param openOrderCount\n   231→     *            The openOrderCount to set\n   232→     */\n   233→    public void setOpenOrderCount(int openOrderCount) {\n   234→        this.openOrderCount = openOrderCount;\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    /**\n   238→     * Gets the deletedOrderCount\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @return Returns a int\n   241→     */\n   242→    public int getDeletedOrderCount() {\n   243→        return deletedOrderCount;\n   244→    }\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Sets the deletedOrderCount\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param deletedOrderCount\n   250→     *            The deletedOrderCount to set\n   251→     */\n   252→    public void setDeletedOrderCount(int deletedOrderCount) {\n   253→        this.deletedOrderCount = deletedOrderCount;\n   254→    }\n   255→\n   256→    /**\n   257→     * Gets the orderCount\n   258→     *\n   259→     * @return Returns a int\n   260→     */\n   261→    public int getOrderCount() {\n   262→        return orderCount;\n   263→    }\n   264→\n   265→    /**\n   266→     * Sets the orderCount\n   267→     *\n   268→     * @param orderCount\n   269→     *            The orderCount to set\n   270→     */\n   271→    public void setOrderCount(int orderCount) {\n   272→        this.orderCount = orderCount;\n   273→    }\n   274→\n   275→    /**\n   276→     * Gets the tradeStockCount\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @return Returns a int\n   279→     */\n   280→    public int getTradeStockCount() {\n   281→        return tradeStockCount;\n   282→    }\n   283→\n   284→    /**\n   285→     * Sets the tradeStockCount\n   286→     *\n   287→     * @param tradeStockCount\n   288→     *            The tradeStockCount to set\n   289→     */\n   290→    public void setTradeStockCount(int tradeStockCount) {\n   291→        this.tradeStockCount = tradeStockCount;\n   292→    }\n   293→\n   294→}\n   295→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"86430a6b-3ddc-42cc-993f-023435ae4716"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F6i5ijUXdXiDEeozVwKMay","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→\n     6→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.given;\n     7→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.is;\n     8→\n     9→@QuarkusTest\n    10→class TradeResourceTest {\n    11→\n    12→    @Test\n    13→    void testMarketSummaryEndpoint() {\n    14→        given()\n    15→            .when().get(\"/rest/trade/market\")\n    16→            .then()\n    17→            .statusCode(200);\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"4e192711-bd86-481c-8b54-2ef9cd834082"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mnirq5pP5hqz1kcYBDgbhw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n    19→import io.restassured.http.ContentType;\n    20→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n    21→\n    22→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.given;\n    23→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.*;\n    24→\n    25→/**\n    26→ * Tests for the messaging functionality.\n    27→ * These tests verify that the JMS-to-Reactive-Messaging migration works correctly.\n    28→ * \n    29→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    30→ * These tests replace manual testing of:\n    31→ * - PingServlet2MDBQueue -> /rest/messaging/ping/broker\n    32→ * - PingServlet2MDBTopic -> /rest/messaging/ping/streamer\n    33→ */\n    34→@QuarkusTest\n    35→public class MessagingResourceTest {\n    36→\n    37→    @Test\n    38→    public void testPingBroker() {\n    39→        given()\n    40→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    41→            .queryParam(\"message\", \"Test ping to broker\")\n    42→        .when()\n    43→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\")\n    44→        .then()\n    45→            .statusCode(200)\n    46→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    47→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-broker-queue\"))\n    48→            .body(\"message\", is(\"Test ping to broker\"));\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    @Test\n    52→    public void testPingBrokerWithDefaultMessage() {\n    53→        given()\n    54→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    55→        .when()\n    56→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\")\n    57→        .then()\n    58→            .statusCode(200)\n    59→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    60→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-broker-queue\"))\n    61→            .body(\"message\", containsString(\"Ping from MessagingResource\"));\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @Test\n    65→    public void testPingStreamer() {\n    66→        given()\n    67→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    68→            .queryParam(\"message\", \"Test ping to streamer\")\n    69→        .when()\n    70→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/streamer\")\n    71→        .then()\n    72→            .statusCode(200)\n    73→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    74→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-streamer-topic\"))\n    75→            .body(\"message\", is(\"Test ping to streamer\"));\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    @Test\n    79→    public void testGetStats() {\n    80→        // First send some messages to generate stats\n    81→        given()\n    82→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    83→        .when()\n    84→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\");\n    85→\n    86→        given()\n    87→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    88→        .when()\n    89→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/streamer\");\n    90→\n    91→        // Wait a bit for async processing\n    92→        try {\n    93→            Thread.sleep(500);\n    94→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    95→            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\n    96→        }\n    97→\n    98→        // Then check stats\n    99→        given()\n   100→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n   101→        .when()\n   102→            .get(\"/rest/messaging/stats\")\n   103→        .then()\n   104→            .statusCode(200)\n   105→            .body(\"statistics\", notNullValue())\n   106→            .body(\"timestamp\", notNullValue());\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Test\n   110→    public void testResetStats() {\n   111→        given()\n   112→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n   113→        .when()\n   114→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/stats/reset\")\n   115→        .then()\n   116→            .statusCode(200)\n   117→            .body(\"status\", is(\"reset\"));\n   118→    }\n   119→}\n   120→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"0ec3a708-8d74-4c13-b5c5-5ef98c4449c7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DwpPs7GeLDHZYZBvVcD66Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n     4→import io.restassured.RestAssured;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→\n     7→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     8→\n     9→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    10→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    11→\n    12→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Tests for JMS to Reactive Messaging migration.\n    16→ * \n    17→ * These tests verify that:\n    18→ * 1. Messages can be sent via MessageProducerService\n    19→ * 2. Messages are received by DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB\n    20→ * 3. MDBStats tracks message processing statistics\n    21→ */\n    22→@QuarkusTest\n    23→public class MessagingTest {\n    24→\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    MessageProducerService messageProducer;\n    27→\n    28→    @Test\n    29→    public void testBrokerPing() throws Exception {\n    30→        // Reset stats\n    31→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    32→        \n    33→        // Send ping message\n    34→        messageProducer.sendBrokerPing(\"Test ping from MessagingTest\");\n    35→        \n    36→        // Give time for async processing\n    37→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    38→        \n    39→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    40→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\");\n    41→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Ping stats should be recorded\");\n    42→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one ping should be processed\");\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    @Test\n    46→    public void testStreamerPing() throws Exception {\n    47→        // Reset stats\n    48→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    49→        \n    50→        // Send ping message to streamer\n    51→        messageProducer.sendStreamerPing(\"Test ping to streamer\");\n    52→        \n    53→        // Give time for async processing\n    54→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    55→        \n    56→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    57→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\");\n    58→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Streamer ping stats should be recorded\");\n    59→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one streamer ping should be processed\");\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @Test\n    63→    public void testQuoteUpdate() throws Exception {\n    64→        // Reset stats\n    65→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    66→        \n    67→        // Publish quote update\n    68→        messageProducer.publishQuoteUpdate(\"s:0\", \n    69→            new java.math.BigDecimal(\"105.50\"), \n    70→            new java.math.BigDecimal(\"100.00\"));\n    71→        \n    72→        // Give time for async processing\n    73→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    74→        \n    75→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    76→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTStreamer3MDB:updateQuote\");\n    77→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Quote update stats should be recorded\");\n    78→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one quote update should be processed\");\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    @Test\n    82→    public void testAsyncOrderProcessing() throws Exception {\n    83→        // First create an order via REST API\n    84→        // The TradeAppResource uses POST to /rest/app with action parameter\n    85→        String loginResponse = RestAssured.given()\n    86→            .formParam(\"action\", \"login\")\n    87→            .formParam(\"uid\", \"uid:0\")\n    88→            .formParam(\"passwd\", \"xxx\")\n    89→            .when()\n    90→            .post(\"/rest/app\")\n    91→            .then()\n    92→            .statusCode(200)\n    93→            .extract().body().asString();\n    94→\n    95→        // Buy a stock (this creates an order)\n    96→        String buyResponse = RestAssured.given()\n    97→            .formParam(\"action\", \"buy\")\n    98→            .formParam(\"symbol\", \"s:0\")\n    99→            .formParam(\"quantity\", \"10\")\n   100→            .when()\n   101→            .post(\"/rest/app\")\n   102→            .then()\n   103→            .statusCode(200)\n   104→            .extract().body().asString();\n   105→\n   106→        assertTrue(buyResponse.contains(\"Order\") || buyResponse.contains(\"order\"), \n   107→            \"Buy should create an order\");\n   108→    }\n   109→}\n   110→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"94d12494-a98b-4803-8d0b-395352c6abfb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzpiEHtyPzE5URJP8as8di","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Complete File Contents\n\nI have successfully read all 36 requested Java files from the DayTrader application. Here are the complete contents organized by category:\n\n### Entity Classes (JPA Entities)\n\n**1. AccountDataBean.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java`\n- JPA entity for user accounts with balance, login/logout counts\n- Uses Jakarta Persistence annotations (@Entity, @Id, @GeneratedValue)\n- Contains relationships to AccountProfileDataBean, OrderDataBean, and HoldingDataBean\n\n**2. AccountProfileDataBean.java** - User profile information\n- Contains user credentials, email, address, credit card info\n- Uses Jakarta validation annotations (@Email, @NotBlank)\n\n**3. HoldingDataBean.java** - Stock holdings entity\n- Represents shares owned by an account\n- Links to AccountDataBean and QuoteDataBean\n\n**4. OrderDataBean.java** - Buy/sell orders\n- Contains order status, type (buy/sell), quantity, price\n- Includes named queries for finding orders by various criteria\n\n**5. QuoteDataBean.java** - Stock quote data\n- Stock symbol, company name, price, volume\n- Named queries for retrieving all quotes and quotes for update\n\n### Implementation Classes\n\n**6. AsyncOrder.java** - Asynchronous order processing\n- Uses @Transactional instead of UserTransaction\n- Runnable for async order completion\n\n**7. AsyncOrderSubmitter.java** - Submits async orders\n- Uses Quarkus ExecutorService with virtual threads\n- Replaced ManagedExecutorService with @VirtualThreads\n\n**8. KeySequenceDirect.java** - Primary key sequence generator\n- Manages key blocks for entity IDs\n- JDBC-based key allocation\n\n**9. TradeDirectDBUtils.java** - Database utility operations\n- Database initialization and reset functions\n- Uses Agroal DataSource (Quarkus)\n- DDL parsing and table creation\n\n**10. AsyncScheduledOrder.java** - Scheduled async order processing\n- EJB3 implementation mode\n- Uses CDI Instance for TradeServices selection\n\n**11. AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java** - Scheduled order submission\n- Uses ExecutorService with delay instead of ManagedScheduledExecutorService\n\n**12. DirectSLSBBean.java** - Session to Direct mode implementation\n- @ApplicationScoped instead of @Stateless\n- Delegates to TradeDirect implementation\n- Uses @Transactional for transaction management\n\n### Interface Definitions\n\n**13. MarketSummaryUpdate.java** - CDI qualifier for market summary updates\n\n**14. QuotePriceChange.java** - CDI qualifier for quote price changes\n\n**15. RuntimeMode.java** - CDI qualifier for runtime mode selection\n\n**16. Trace.java** - Interceptor binding for tracing\n\n**17. TradeDB.java** - Database operations interface\n- resetTrade() and checkDBProductName() methods\n\n**18. TradeEJB.java** - CDI qualifier for EJB implementation\n\n**19. TradeJDBC.java** - CDI qualifier for JDBC implementation\n\n**20. TradeServices.java** - Main business interface\n- All trading operations: buy, sell, login, register, etc.\n- Market summary, quotes, holdings, orders\n\n**21. TradeSession2Direct.java** - CDI qualifier for Session to Direct mode\n\n### Messaging Classes\n\n**22. OrderMessage.java** - Order message POJO\n- Replaced JMS TextMessage with plain Java object\n- Contains command, orderID, twoPhase, publishTime\n- Factory methods for newOrder() and ping()\n\n**23. QuoteUpdateMessage.java** - Quote update message POJO\n- Replaced JMS message for quote price updates\n- Contains symbol, price, oldPrice, company info\n\n### Utility Classes\n\n**24. FinancialUtils.java** - Financial calculations\n- Gain/loss computations\n- HTML formatting for financial data\n- Uses RoundingMode enum (not deprecated BigDecimal constants)\n\n**25. KeyBlock.java** - Key block iterator\n- Manages ranges of primary keys\n- Extends AbstractSequentialList\n\n**26. Log.java** - Logging utility\n- Wrapper around java.util.logging.Logger\n- Various log/error/trace methods\n\n**27. MDBStats.java** - MDB statistics tracker\n- HashMap-based singleton for message timing stats\n- Tracks min/max/average processing times\n\n**28. RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java** - Recent quote changes\n- Thread-safe list using CopyOnWriteArrayList\n- Fires CDI events for price changes\n- Used by WebSocket and SSE\n\n**29. TimerStat.java** - Timing statistics bean\n- Tracks count, min, max, total time\n- Calculates averages\n\n**30. TradeConfig.java** - Application configuration\n- Runtime modes: Direct JPA, Direct JDBC, EJB3, Session to Direct\n- Order processing modes: Sync, Async, Async 2-Phase\n- Database scaling parameters (MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES)\n- Random data generators\n\n**31. TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java** - CDI AnnotationLiteral\n- For programmatic qualifier selection\n\n### Bean Classes\n\n**32. MarketSummaryDataBean.java** - Market summary data\n- TSIA (Trade Stock Index Average)\n- Top gainers/losers\n- Volume information\n\n**33. RunStatsDataBean.java** - Database reset statistics\n- User counts, order counts, holding counts\n- Login/logout statistics\n\n### Test Classes\n\n**34. TradeResourceTest.java** - REST endpoint test\n- Tests /rest/trade/market endpoint\n- Uses Quarkus testing framework\n\n**35. MessagingResourceTest.java** - Messaging REST tests\n- Tests broker and streamer ping endpoints\n- Tests statistics retrieval and reset\n\n**36. MessagingTest.java** - Messaging functionality tests\n- Tests message sending/receiving\n- Verifies MDBStats tracking\n- Tests async order processing\n\n## Migration Patterns Observed\n\nThe code shows a migration from Jakarta EE to Quarkus with these key changes:\n\n1. **Dependency Injection**: javax.* → jakarta.* packages\n2. **EJB → CDI**: @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, or @Dependent\n3. **Transactions**: @TransactionAttribute → @Transactional\n4. **Concurrency**: ManagedExecutorService → Quarkus ExecutorService with @VirtualThreads\n5. **Messaging**: JMS → Reactive Messaging with POJOs\n6. **DataSource**: @Resource DataSource → @Inject AgroalDataSource\n7. **Validation**: Bean Validation 2.0 → 3.0 (Jakarta)\n\nAll files have been successfully retrieved with complete contents."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"b2dc5cac-7d4f-4788-b989-001aa2ecb3e3"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MecSiAJi7WuALRMmz2Lpjc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me plan and execute the migration. The key Quarkus-specific components that need to be changed are:\n\n1. `io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent` → Jakarta EE `@PostConstruct` / `@Startup`\n2. `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled` → Jakarta EE `@Schedule`\n3. `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.*` → Jakarta JMS\n4. `io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction` → standard JTA\n5. `io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast` → removed\n6. Quarkus-specific DataSource → standard Jakarta resource injection\n7. `@VirtualThreads` → standard ManagedExecutorService\n8. `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty` → standard configuration\n\nThe target Jakarta EE platform will be **Open Liberty** since this was originally an IBM WebSphere/Liberty application (DayTrader). Let me now execute the migration."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9909,"cache_read_input_tokens":89256,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9909,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":677},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"9990be2c-1160-437c-834f-c517ae5622b6"}
