{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WmHo8zREfXAR1DizD4RdUx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    24→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    25→\n    26→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n    38→ * This replaces the manual \"Populate Database\" action from the Jakarta EE version.\n    39→ */\n    40→@ApplicationScoped\n    41→public class DatabasePopulator {\n    42→\n    43→    @Inject\n    44→    EntityManager em;\n    45→\n    46→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    47→    boolean populateOnStartup;\n    48→\n    49→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    50→    int maxUsers;\n    51→\n    52→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    53→    int maxQuotes;\n    54→\n    55→    @Transactional\n    56→    void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    57→        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n    58→            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n    59→            return;\n    60→        }\n    61→\n    62→        // Check if database already has data (using native SQL since entity names are lowercase)\n    63→        Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n    64→        if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n    65→            Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n    66→            return;\n    67→        }\n    68→\n    69→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n    70→        \n    71→        try {\n    72→            populateQuotes();\n    73→            populateUsers();\n    74→            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    75→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    76→            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    private void populateQuotes() {\n    81→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n    82→        \n    83→        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n    84→            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n    85→            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n    86→            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n    87→            \n    88→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n    89→            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n    90→            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n    91→            quote.setPrice(price);\n    92→            quote.setOpen(price);\n    93→            quote.setLow(price);\n    94→            quote.setHigh(price);\n    95→            quote.setChange(0.0);\n    96→            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n    97→            \n    98→            em.persist(quote);\n    99→            \n   100→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   101→                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n   102→            }\n   103→        }\n   104→        em.flush();\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    private void populateUsers() {\n   108→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n   109→        \n   110→        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n   111→            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   112→            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   113→            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   114→            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   115→            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   116→            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n   117→            \n   118→            if (i == 0) {\n   119→                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000); // uid:0 starts with a cool million.\n   120→            }\n   121→            \n   122→            // Create profile\n   123→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   124→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   125→            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n   126→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   127→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   128→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   129→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   130→            em.persist(profile);\n   131→            \n   132→            // Create account\n   133→            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n   134→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   135→            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   136→            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   137→            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n   138→            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n   139→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   140→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   141→            em.persist(account);\n   142→            \n   143→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   144→                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n   145→            }\n   146→        }\n   147→        em.flush();\n   148→    }\n   149→}\n   150→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y2nJW7yt9C5MjdsJWqbFAg","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"3fc2ca4d-bf06-4aae-a4ce-96745534d66f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SXrhyKP6uNiisttf3BNYZ8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→\n    22→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    23→// MIGRATION: @Singleton EJB -> @ApplicationScoped CDI\n    24→// MIGRATION: @Schedule -> @Scheduled (Quarkus)\n    25→// MIGRATION: @Lock -> synchronized methods\n    26→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    27→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    28→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    34→\n    35→import io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n    36→\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→\n    44→// MIGRATION: @Singleton EJB -> @ApplicationScoped CDI bean\n    45→@ApplicationScoped\n    46→public class MarketSummarySingleton {\n    47→\n    48→  private volatile MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n    49→\n    50→  @Inject\n    51→  EntityManager entityManager;\n    52→  \n    53→  @Inject\n    54→  @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    55→  Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    56→  \n    57→  // MIGRATION: ManagedExecutorService removed, use simple fireAsync()\n    58→  \n    59→\n    60→  /* Update Market Summary every 20 seconds */\n    61→  // MIGRATION: @Schedule -> @Scheduled (Quarkus)\n    62→  @Scheduled(every = \"20s\")\n    63→  void updateMarketSummary() { \n    64→\n    65→\n    66→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    67→\n    68→\n    69→    if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3)\n    70→    {\n    71→      Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating periodically\");\n    72→      return; // Only do the periodic update if in EJB3 Mode\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    computeMarketSummary();\n    76→    // MIGRATION: ManagedExecutorService removed, use simple fireAsync()\n    77→    mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\");\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  // MIGRATION: @Lock(READ) -> synchronized getter (volatile field provides visibility)\n    81→  public synchronized MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() { \n    82→    if (marketSummaryDataBean == null){\n    83→      // Compute market summary on first access regardless of mode\n    84→      computeMarketSummary();\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    return marketSummaryDataBean;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  // Internal method to compute market summary (called on-demand or by scheduler)\n    91→  private void computeMarketSummary() {\n    92→    List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    93→\n    94→    try {        \n    95→      // Find Trade Stock Index Quotes (Top 100 quotes) ordered by their change in value\n    96→      CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    97→      CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    98→      Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    99→      criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n   100→      criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n   101→      TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n   102→      quotes = q.getResultList();\n   103→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   104→      Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured. If this is the first time the application has been started, please create and populate the database tables. Then restart the server.\");\n   105→      return;\n   106→    }\t\n   107→\n   108→    /* TODO: Make this cleaner? */\n   109→    QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n   110→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   111→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   112→    BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   113→    BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   114→    double totalVolume = 0.0;\n   115→\n   116→    if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n   117→      for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   118→        topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   119→      }\n   120→      for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n   121→        topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   122→      }\n   123→\n   124→      for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n   125→        BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   126→        BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n   127→        double volume = quote.getVolume();\n   128→        TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n   129→        openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n   130→        totalVolume += volume;\n   131→      }\n   132→      TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   133→      openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  // MIGRATION: @Lock(WRITE) -> synchronized setter\n   140→  public synchronized void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n   141→    this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n   142→  }\n   143→\n   144→}\n   145→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y2nJW7yt9C5MjdsJWqbFAg","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"2c8ed579-b908-46ad-a6c0-64dc38a0cb61"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XHvcSt7RUw3LKPiQrDvJzP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    22→\n    23→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\n    24→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n    25→\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    27→\n    28→/**\n    29→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    30→ * \n    31→ * Original (Jakarta EE - JMS Producer Pattern):\n    32→ * ---------------------------------------------\n    33→ * @Resource(name = \"jms/QueueConnectionFactory\")\n    34→ * private ConnectionFactory queueConnectionFactory;\n    35→ * \n    36→ * @Resource(name = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n    37→ * private Queue tradeBrokerQueue;\n    38→ * \n    39→ * // Usage:\n    40→ * JMSContext context = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();\n    41→ * TextMessage message = context.createTextMessage();\n    42→ * message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\");\n    43→ * message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID);\n    44→ * message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase);\n    45→ * message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    46→ * message.setText(\"Order message...\");\n    47→ * context.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n    48→ * \n    49→ * Quarkus (SmallRye Reactive Messaging - Emitter Pattern):\n    50→ * --------------------------------------------------------\n    51→ * @Inject\n    52→ * @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    53→ * Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter;\n    54→ * \n    55→ * // Usage:\n    56→ * OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    57→ * brokerEmitter.send(message);\n    58→ * \n    59→ * Key Differences:\n    60→ * 1. No ConnectionFactory/JMSContext - just @Channel + Emitter\n    61→ * 2. No manual message creation - just create POJO\n    62→ * 3. No explicit property setting - POJO fields are the properties\n    63→ * 4. Cleaner, more type-safe code\n    64→ * 5. Built-in backpressure handling\n    65→ */\n    66→@ApplicationScoped\n    67→public class MessageProducerService {\n    68→\n    69→    @Inject\n    70→    @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    71→    @io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast\n    72→    Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter;\n    73→\n    74→    @Inject\n    75→    @Channel(\"trade-streamer-topic\")\n    76→    @io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast\n    77→    Emitter<QuoteUpdateMessage> streamerEmitter;\n    78→\n    79→    /**\n    80→     * Queue a new order for asynchronous processing.\n    81→     * This replaces the JMS Queue send in the original DTBroker pattern.\n    82→     * \n    83→     * @param orderID the order ID to process\n    84→     * @param twoPhase whether to use two-phase commit\n    85→     */\n    86→    public void queueOrderForProcessing(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    87→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    88→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:queueOrderForProcessing - sending order \" + orderID);\n    89→        brokerEmitter.send(message);\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    /**\n    93→     * Send a ping message to the trade broker queue.\n    94→     * Used for testing and performance measurement.\n    95→     * \n    96→     * @param text the ping message text\n    97→     */\n    98→    public void sendBrokerPing(String text) {\n    99→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.ping(text);\n   100→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendBrokerPing - sending ping\");\n   101→        brokerEmitter.send(message);\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * Publish a quote update to the streamer topic.\n   106→     * This replaces the JMS Topic publish in the original DTStreamer pattern.\n   107→     * \n   108→     * @param symbol the stock symbol\n   109→     * @param newPrice the new price\n   110→     * @param oldPrice the old price\n   111→     */\n   112→    public void publishQuoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n   113→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, newPrice, oldPrice);\n   114→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuoteUpdate - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n   115→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    /**\n   119→     * Publish a complete quote price change to the streamer topic.\n   120→     * This replaces the full JMS Topic publish in the original TradeDirect pattern.\n   121→     */\n   122→    public void publishQuotePriceChange(String symbol, String company, BigDecimal price,\n   123→            BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high,\n   124→            double volume, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n   125→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, price, oldPrice);\n   126→        message.setCompany(company);\n   127→        message.setOpen(open);\n   128→        message.setLow(low);\n   129→        message.setHigh(high);\n   130→        message.setVolume(volume);\n   131→        message.setChangeFactor(changeFactor);\n   132→        message.setSharesTraded(sharesTraded);\n   133→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuotePriceChange - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n   134→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   135→    }\n   136→\n   137→    /**\n   138→     * Send a ping message to the streamer topic.\n   139→     * Used for testing and performance measurement.\n   140→     * \n   141→     * @param text the ping message text\n   142→     */\n   143→    public void sendStreamerPing(String text) {\n   144→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.ping(text);\n   145→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendStreamerPing - sending ping\");\n   146→        streamerEmitter.send(message);\n   147→    }\n   148→}\n   149→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y2nJW7yt9C5MjdsJWqbFAg","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"06f7b8f5-ce8d-49ce-b0f4-40e6cdac665b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018J5jc6gFiNAWpoG2MAeYdt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    20→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    21→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    22→\n    23→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.OrderMessage;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    30→\n    31→/**\n    32→ * Message-Driven Bean for processing trade orders.\n    33→ * \n    34→ * MIGRATION NOTES - Original Jakarta EE annotations:\n    35→ * --------------------------------------------------\n    36→ * @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    37→ * @TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    38→ * @MessageDriven(activationConfig = { \n    39→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"acknowledgeMode\", propertyValue = \"Auto-acknowledge\"),\n    40→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Queue\"),\n    41→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\"),\n    42→ *     @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"subscriptionDurability\", propertyValue = \"NonDurable\") \n    43→ * })\n    44→ * public class DTBroker3MDB implements MessageListener { ... }\n    45→ * \n    46→ * Quarkus Migration:\n    47→ * ------------------\n    48→ * @ApplicationScoped replaces @MessageDriven\n    49→ * @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\") replaces JMS destination config\n    50→ * @Transactional replaces @TransactionAttribute\n    51→ * OrderMessage POJO replaces JMS TextMessage\n    52→ */\n    53→@ApplicationScoped\n    54→public class DTBroker3MDB {\n    55→  \n    56→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    57→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    58→\n    59→  // MIGRATION: @Resource MessageDrivenContext mdc -> Exception propagation for rollback\n    60→  // In Quarkus, throwing an exception triggers rollback instead of mdc.setRollbackOnly()\n    61→\n    62→  @Inject\n    63→  TradeServices trade;\n    64→\n    65→  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    66→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    67→      statInterval = 10000;\n    68→    }\n    69→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    70→  }   \n    71→\n    72→  @PostConstruct\n    73→  void init() {\n    74→    Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:init()\");\n    75→  } \n    76→  \n    77→  /**\n    78→   * Process incoming order messages.\n    79→   * \n    80→   * MIGRATION: This replaces the JMS MessageListener.onMessage(Message) method.\n    81→   * - JMS TextMessage -> OrderMessage POJO\n    82→   * - message.getStringProperty(\"command\") -> message.getCommand()\n    83→   * - message.getIntProperty(\"orderID\") -> message.getOrderID()\n    84→   * - message.getBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\") -> message.isTwoPhase()\n    85→   * - message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\") -> message.getPublishTime()\n    86→   */\n    87→  @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n    88→  @Transactional\n    89→  public void onMessage(OrderMessage message) {\n    90→    try {\n    91→\n    92→      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n    93→          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n    94→\n    95→      // MIGRATION: JMS redelivery check removed - Quarkus handles redelivery differently\n    96→      // if (message.getJMSRedelivered()) { ... }\n    97→\n    98→      String command = message.getCommand();\n    99→      if (command == null) {\n   100→        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n   101→        return;\n   102→      }\n   103→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n   104→        /* Get the Order ID and complete the Order */\n   105→        Integer orderID = message.getOrderID();\n   106→        boolean twoPhase = message.isTwoPhase();\n   107→        // MIGRATION: 'direct' property removed - not used in Quarkus version\n   108→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n   109→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   110→\n   111→        try {\n   112→          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n   113→\n   114→          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   115→\n   116→          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   117→\n   118→          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   119→            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n   120→                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   121→                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n   122→                \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   123→                \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   124→                \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   125→          }\n   126→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   127→          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n   128→          // MIGRATION: mdc.setRollbackOnly() -> throw RuntimeException\n   129→          throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to complete order: \" + orderID, e);\n   130→        }\n   131→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n   132→\n   133→        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n   134→\n   135→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n   136→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   137→\n   138→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   139→\n   140→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   141→          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n   142→              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   143→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   144→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   145→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   146→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   147→        }\n   148→      } else {\n   149→        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n   150→      }\n   151→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   152→      // JMS onMessage should handle all exceptions\n   153→      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Exception\", t);\n   154→      // MIGRATION: mdc.setRollbackOnly() -> throw RuntimeException  \n   155→      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTBroker3MDB processing failed\", t);\n   156→    }\n   157→  }\n   158→}\n   159→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y2nJW7yt9C5MjdsJWqbFAg","session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"7e89db2b-085d-4bef-8963-e73b0e8bf99d"}
