{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01STnj6481SKQXUGD2xyfY7g","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     3→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     5→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     6→\n     7→    <groupId>io.openliberty.samples</groupId>\n     8→    <artifactId>daytrader-jakarta</artifactId>\n     9→    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    10→    <packaging>war</packaging>\n    11→\n    12→    <properties>\n    13→        <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n    14→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    15→        <liberty.var.default.http.port>8080</liberty.var.default.http.port>\n    16→    </properties>\n    17→\n    18→    <dependencies>\n    19→        <dependency>\n    20→            <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n    21→            <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n    22→            <version>10.0.0</version>\n    23→            <scope>provided</scope>\n    24→        </dependency>\n    25→        <dependency>\n    26→            <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    27→            <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    28→            <version>2.2.224</version>\n    29→            <scope>compile</scope>\n    30→        </dependency>\n    31→    </dependencies>\n    32→\n    33→    <build>\n    34→        <finalName>daytrader</finalName>\n    35→        <plugins>\n    36→            <plugin>\n    37→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    38→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n    39→                <version>3.13.0</version>\n    40→                <configuration>\n    41→                    <release>17</release>\n    42→                </configuration>\n    43→            </plugin>\n    44→            <plugin>\n    45→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    46→                <artifactId>maven-war-plugin</artifactId>\n    47→                <version>3.4.0</version>\n    48→            </plugin>\n    49→            <plugin>\n    50→                <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    51→                <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    52→                <version>3.10</version>\n    53→            </plugin>\n    54→        </plugins>\n    55→    </build>\n    56→</project>\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"72e1151c-3a49-4cc3-b237-31706f90af65"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017U3g1AdCUr4aFWNNeMa6QU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n     2→\n     3→WORKDIR /app\n     4→COPY . .\n     5→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi\n     6→RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n     7→\n     8→FROM icr.io/appcafe/open-liberty:full-java17-openj9-ubi\n     9→\n    10→USER root\n    11→# Install Python for smoke tests\n    12→RUN dnf install -y python3 python3-pip curl && dnf clean all\n    13→\n    14→# Copy Liberty configuration\n    15→COPY --from=builder /app/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml /config/server.xml\n    16→\n    17→# Copy H2 driver to Liberty shared lib\n    18→RUN mkdir -p /config/lib\n    19→COPY --from=builder /app/target/daytrader/WEB-INF/lib/h2-*.jar /config/lib/\n    20→\n    21→# Copy the WAR file\n    22→COPY --from=builder /app/target/daytrader.war /config/apps/daytrader.war\n    23→\n    24→# Copy static resources and smoke test\n    25→COPY --from=builder /app/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/ /config/apps/expanded/daytrader.war/\n    26→\n    27→# Copy smoke test if exists\n    28→COPY --from=builder /app/smoke.py /app/smoke.py\n    29→\n    30→USER 1001\n    31→EXPOSE 8080\n    32→\n    33→CMD [\"/opt/ol/wlp/bin/server\", \"run\", \"defaultServer\"]\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"c2ab7b40-6e97-4c52-82d8-4fb1b5d5a065"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LEJNnP62xZWvjZz22vnj7b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"DayTrader Jakarta EE\">\n     3→    <featureManager>\n     4→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     5→    </featureManager>\n     6→\n     7→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" httpPort=\"8080\" httpsPort=\"9443\" host=\"*\"/>\n     8→\n     9→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    10→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2-*.jar\"/>\n    11→    </library>\n    12→\n    13→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/TradeDataSource\">\n    14→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    15→        <properties.h2.embedded databaseName=\"mem:tradedb\" createDatabase=\"true\" user=\"sa\" password=\"\"/>\n    16→    </dataSource>\n    17→\n    18→    <webApplication location=\"daytrader.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n    19→        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    20→    </webApplication>\n    21→</server>\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"bd93ced1-5c11-4743-8976-228c9c401955"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016hsM594VNet1n9RfMgkmy1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<persistence version=\"3.0\" xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\"\n     3→             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence/persistence_3_0.xsd\">\n     5→    <persistence-unit name=\"daytrader\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n     6→        <jta-data-source>jdbc/TradeDataSource</jta-data-source>\n     7→        <class>com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean</class>\n     8→        <class>com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean</class>\n     9→        <class>com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean</class>\n    10→        <class>com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean</class>\n    11→        <class>com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean</class>\n    12→        <properties>\n    13→            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"drop-and-create\"/>\n    14→            <property name=\"hibernate.dialect\" value=\"org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\"/>\n    15→        </properties>\n    16→    </persistence-unit>\n    17→</persistence>\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"ba1c137b-6442-4499-80a4-8825f2b98af7"}
