{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EUSxPiGLnMNCJ1M1JALpey","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two issues:\n1. The `GenerationType.IDENTITY` creates `INTEGER IDENTITY NOT NULL` which isn't valid H2 syntax. I need to change to `GenerationType.AUTO` or use `GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`.\n2. There's an ORB user registry warning about EJB.\n\nThe main issue is the IDENTITY generation. EclipseLink generates `INTEGER IDENTITY` for H2 which H2 v2 doesn't support. I need to switch the generation strategy. Let me fix this:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":103630,"cache_read_input_tokens":14809,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":103630,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":208},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"f38b2be8-325a-4d20-9391-64aeddb93812"}
