{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Mv72mFhE4UsxVVpfw614HE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is that EclipseLink with `GenerationType.IDENTITY` generates `INTEGER IDENTITY` which is old H2 syntax. H2 v2 uses `GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`. I should switch to `GenerationType.AUTO` which will use `IDENTITY` column-level syntax correctly, or use `SEQUENCE` strategy. The cleanest fix is to change the generation strategy to `GenerationType.AUTO` and let EclipseLink handle it. But actually, the cleaner fix is to use `GenerationType.SEQUENCE` which EclipseLink handles well with H2.\n\nActually, let me just change to `GenerationType.AUTO` which should work with EclipseLink + H2. EclipseLink will use a SEQUENCE strategy for AUTO:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":480,"cache_read_input_tokens":118971,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":480,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":320},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"5155f536-01d3-42bf-9e95-3e2bff7bb311"}
