{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CKkzZzeckR8ZiFNtgBsUCj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is `\"account\" is null` meaning `profile.getAccount()` returns null. The EAGER fetch didn't help. The problem is that EclipseLink `OneToOne` with `mappedBy` still depends on the foreign key being on the Account table side. Let me check the login logic more carefully.\n\nThe issue is likely in the data population. The `DatabasePopulator` persists profile first, then account with `account.setProfile(profile)`. But it never calls `profile.setAccount(account)`. After persistence, the in-memory objects are detached. When querying again, EclipseLink should find the reverse relationship through the FK. But perhaps the mapping is not working because of a cache or weaving issue.\n\nLet me modify the approach - instead of relying on `profile.getAccount()`, I'll modify the `login`, `getAccountData`, and `logout` methods in TradeSLSBBean to use a JPQL query to find the account by profile:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":671,"cache_read_input_tokens":143956,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":671,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":392},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dc8c70c-c917-4a3c-9449-19451948009a","uuid":"627caf52-258c-4160-a5fc-e34bc907f446"}
